</strong>A vessel\'s natural radar cross section can be very small — especially fiberglass or wooden hulls. The RS470-Z\'s <strong>≥ 40 m² RCS</strong> dramatically increases the vessel\'s radar "footprint," making it appear as a much larger and more detectable target on surrounding ships\' radar screens — a critical factor in preventing collisions in low visibility, fog, or night-time conditions.</div>',
