                'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Hydrostatic Release Unit QJG-A. Automatic Float-Free Life Raft Deployment in Marine Emergencies.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>QJG-A Hydrostatic Release Unit (HRU)</strong> is a critical automatic safety device that triggers the release of a life raft from its cradle when a vessel sinks to a depth of <strong>2 to 4 meters</strong>. Constructed from marine-grade <strong>stainless steel</strong>, it activates purely by water pressure — requiring no electrical power, manual intervention, or crew action. Certified by <strong>CCS or Qualified Certificate</strong> and an essential SOLAS compliance fitting for any vessel carrying an inflatable life raft.</p><div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-12"><div class="rounded-xl border-2 border-cyan-400 bg-cyan-50 p-5 text-center"><div class="text-2xl font-bold text-cyan-700">2 – 4 m</div><div class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-2">Release Depth</div><div class="text-slate-400 text-xs mt-1">Activates automatically at this depth</div></div><div class="rounded-xl border-2 border-cyan-400 bg-cyan-50 p-5 text-center"><div class="text-2xl font-bold text-cyan-700">10 kN</div><div class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-2">Tensile Strength</div><div class="text-slate-400 text-xs mt-1">Breaking load resistance</div></div><div class="rounded-xl border-2 border-cyan-400 bg-cyan-50 p-5 text-center"><div class="text-2xl font-bold text-cyan-700">SS</div><div class="text-slate-600 text-sm mt-2">Stainless Steel</div><div class="text-slate-400 text-xs mt-1">Marine-grade material</div></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Product Specifications</h2><div class="mb-12 rounded-xl overflow-hidden border border-slate-200"><div class="grid grid-cols-2 bg-cyan-600 text-white text-sm font-semibold px-4 py-3"><div>Specification</div><div>Details</div></div><div class="grid grid-cols-2 px-4 py-3 bg-white border-b border-slate-100 text-sm text-slate-700"><div class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Model</div><div>QJG-A</div></div><div class="grid grid-cols-2 px-4 py-3 bg-slate-50 border-b border-slate-100 text-sm text-slate-700"><div class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Main Material</div><div>Stainless Steel</div></div><div class="grid grid-cols-2 px-4 py-3 bg-white border-b border-slate-100 text-sm text-slate-700"><div class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Release Depth</div><div>2 – 4 m below water surface</div></div><div class="grid grid-cols-2 px-4 py-3 bg-slate-50 border-b border-slate-100 text-sm text-slate-700"><div class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Tensile Strength</div><div>10 kN</div></div><div class="grid grid-cols-2 px-4 py-3 bg-white text-sm text-slate-700"><div class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Certificate</div><div>CCS or Qualified Certificate</div></div></div><div class="my-8 bg-cyan-700 text-white rounded-xl p-6 flex gap-4 items-start"><div class="text-3xl mt-1">⚙️</div><div><h3 class="text-base font-bold mb-1">How the HRU Works</h3><p class="text-cyan-100 text-sm leading-relaxed">When a vessel sinks to a depth of <strong class="text-white">2 to 4 meters</strong>, water pressure automatically triggers the HRU mechanism, cutting the lashing that secures the life raft to its cradle. The life raft canister then <strong class="text-white">floats free to the surface</strong>, where the painter line — still attached to the sinking vessel — pulls taut and inflates the raft automatically. The painter line then breaks free at a set tension, leaving the inflated raft on the surface ready for survivors.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Fully Automatic Operation:</strong> Activates by water pressure alone — no electricity, no manual action, and no crew intervention required</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Precise Release Depth — 2 to 4 m:</strong> Triggers at the correct depth to allow the life raft sufficient time to float free and inflate before sinking further</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">High Tensile Strength — 10 kN:</strong> Withstands the forces of rough seas and vessel movement without accidental release during normal operations</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Marine-Grade Stainless Steel:</strong> Corrosion-resistant construction ensures reliable performance after prolonged deck exposure to saltwater and UV</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Cradle &amp; Painter Line Compatible:</strong> Designed to work seamlessly with standard life raft cradles and painter line systems</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Dual Certified:</strong> CCS or Qualified Certificate ensures compliance with international SOLAS life-saving appliance requirements</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-amber-50 border-l-4 border-amber-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-amber-800 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold mb-1">⚠️ Important Notice</strong>The HRU has a <strong>mandatory replacement interval</strong> — typically every 2 years or as specified by the manufacturer and flag state authority. An expired HRU <strong>may fail to activate</strong> when needed. Always check the expiry date during routine life raft servicing inspections and replace immediately if expired. Never attempt to manually disassemble or reuse a deployed unit.</div>',
