                'image'       => '/images/products/manual-pump.png',
                'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Manual Pump. Essential Hand-Operated Bilge and Inflation Pump for Marine Survival Equipment.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>Marine Manual Pump</strong> is a reliable, hand-operated pumping device designed for use aboard life rafts, lifeboats, and other marine survival craft. Requiring no electrical power or external pressure source, it serves two critical functions at sea — <strong>removing accumulated water (bilge pumping)</strong> from inside the survival craft to keep it safe and stable, and <strong>topping up air pressure</strong> in the inflatable tubes of life rafts when pressure drops due to temperature changes or minor leakage. A standard inclusion in SOLAS Pack A and Pack B life raft survival kits.</p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Primary Functions</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12"><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">💧</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Bilge Pumping</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Manually removes water that enters the life raft through waves, rain, or splash. Keeping the raft floor dry reduces hypothermia risk and maintains the stability and buoyancy of the survival craft.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🌬️</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Tube Inflation Top-Up</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Restores air pressure in life raft buoyancy tubes when pressure decreases due to cold temperatures or minor slow leaks, ensuring the raft maintains full structural integrity throughout survival.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">No Power Required:</strong> Fully hand-operated — functions independently of batteries, electricity, or fuel sources</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Dual-Purpose Design:</strong> Suitable for both water removal and air inflation without additional tools or attachments</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Lightweight &amp; Compact:</strong> Small enough to store efficiently inside a life raft survival kit without taking up valuable space</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Durable Construction:</strong> Built to withstand saltwater exposure, UV, and the physical demands of emergency use at sea</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Easy to Operate:</strong> Simple reciprocating action requires no training — usable by any survivor regardless of experience</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">SOLAS Kit Compliant:</strong> Standard required equipment in life raft SOLAS Pack A and Pack B survival kits</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>Rinse the pump with fresh water after each use or exposure to saltwater to prevent corrosion of internal components and valve seats. Inspect the pump and its valves during <strong>annual life raft servicing</strong> to ensure the seals remain airtight and the plunger action is smooth. Replace immediately if cracking, stiffness, or loss of suction is detected.</div>',

