                'image'       => '/images/products/co2-cylinder.png',
                'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Marine CO2 Cylinder. SOLAS-Approved Automatic Inflation Cylinder for Life Raft Deployment.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>HYPRO Marine CO2 Cylinder</strong> is a high-pressure gas cylinder engineered for the automatic inflation of life rafts during emergency deployment at sea. Available in <strong>3L, 5L, 6L, and 7L</strong> capacities, this cylinder provides the instantaneous burst of CO2 gas required to fully inflate a life raft within seconds of activation — a critical function when every moment counts in a maritime emergency. Manufactured to <strong>SOLAS standards</strong>, it is a core component of any compliant life raft inflation system.</p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Primary Functions</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12"><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">💨</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Automatic Raft Inflation</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Releases a precise volume of CO2 gas upon activation, fully inflating the life raft buoyancy chambers within seconds — enabling rapid deployment even in severe sea conditions without manual effort.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🛟</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Emergency Readiness</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Keeps the life raft in a constant state of deployment readiness. The sealed, pressurized cylinder ensures gas integrity is maintained throughout the raft\'s service life until emergency activation.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">SOLAS Approved:</strong> Meets international maritime safety regulations for use in certified life raft inflation systems</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Multiple Capacities:</strong> Available in 3L, 5L, 6L, and 7L sizes to suit a wide range of life raft models and passenger capacities</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Instant Activation:</strong> High-pressure CO2 release inflates the raft rapidly upon deployment — no manual pumping or external power required</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Robust Construction:</strong> Heavy-duty cylinder material withstands the corrosive marine environment, pressure stresses, and long-term storage conditions</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Sealed &amp; Pressure-Tested:</strong> Factory-filled and tested to ensure accurate gas charge and leak-free integrity throughout the service interval</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Direct Replacement Compatible:</strong> Designed for straightforward replacement during scheduled life raft servicing with no special tools required</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>The CO2 cylinder must be inspected and replaced according to the manufacturer\'s service schedule — typically during <strong>annual life raft servicing</strong> by a certified service station. Check cylinder weight against the stamped filled weight to verify gas charge has not been lost. Never attempt to recharge, modify, or operate the cylinder outside of its intended life raft inflation system.</div>',
