                'name'        => 'Hand Pump',
                'category'    => 'Emergency Life Raft Equipments',
                'image'       => '/images/products/hand-pump.png',
                'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Marine Hand Pump. Heavy-Duty Rotary Hand Pump for Bilge Drainage and Fluid Transfer at Sea.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>Marine Hand Pump</strong> is a robust, manually operated rotary pump designed for reliable fluid transfer and bilge drainage aboard vessels, life rafts, lifeboats, and other marine craft. Featuring a <strong>ergonomic lever handle with stainless steel shaft</strong> and a compact circular pump body with a bottom discharge port, this pump delivers efficient fluid movement with every stroke — requiring no electricity, batteries, or engine power to operate. Built for demanding marine environments, it is an essential piece of safety and utility equipment for any vessel.</p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Primary Functions</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12"><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">💧</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Bilge Drainage</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Effectively removes unwanted water accumulation from the bilge of vessels and survival craft. Keeping bilge areas clear reduces flooding risk, maintains stability, and improves overall vessel safety.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🔄</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Fluid Transfer</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Suitable for transferring water, light fuels, and other marine fluids between tanks or overboard. The rotary diaphragm mechanism provides consistent flow output with smooth, controlled lever action.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Rotary Lever Design:</strong> Ergonomic handle with stainless steel shaft provides comfortable, high-torque operation with minimal physical effort</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">No Power Required:</strong> Fully manual operation — completely independent of electrical systems, making it reliable during power failures or emergencies</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Corrosion-Resistant Construction:</strong> Heavy-duty black polymer body and stainless steel components designed to withstand prolonged saltwater exposure and UV degradation</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Bottom Discharge Port:</strong> Conveniently located outlet allows direct hose connection for efficient directional fluid discharge overboard or into containers</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Flat Mounting Base:</strong> Integrated flat base plate allows secure deck or bulkhead mounting for permanent installation aboard vessels</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Simple Operation:</strong> Intuitive lever-and-rotate action requires no technical training — operable by any crew member in an emergency situation</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>After each use, flush the pump thoroughly with fresh water to remove salt deposits and debris from internal valves and diaphragm. Periodically inspect the lever shaft, seals, and discharge port for wear or cracking. Lubricate moving parts with marine-grade grease during <strong>routine vessel maintenance</strong> to ensure smooth operation and extend service life. Replace worn seals or diaphragms immediately to maintain pumping efficiency.</div>',
