            [
                'name'        => 'Thermal Protective Aid',
                'category'    => 'Emergency Life Raft Equipments',
                'image'       => '/images/products/thermal-protective-aid.png',
                'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Thermal Protective Aid (TPA). SOLAS-Approved Emergency Heat Retention Blanket for Life Raft Survival Kits.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>Thermal Protective Aid (TPA)</strong> is a lightweight, single-use emergency blanket constructed from <strong>aluminized reflective film</strong> designed to protect survivors from the life-threatening effects of hypothermia and heat loss following immersion or exposure at sea. Weighing just <strong>85 grams</strong>, this compact survival essential reflects and retains the body\'s natural heat, significantly slowing the onset of hypothermia in cold or wet conditions. A mandatory item under <strong>SOLAS regulations</strong>, it is a standard inclusion in life raft survival kits carried aboard commercial vessels, passenger ships, and offshore installations worldwide.</p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Primary Functions</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12"><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🌡️</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Hypothermia Prevention</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Wraps around the survivor\'s body to reflect and retain radiated body heat, dramatically reducing heat loss caused by wind, rain, spray, and cold air exposure. Critical for extending survival time in cold marine environments.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🛡️</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Wind &amp; Moisture Shield</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">The aluminized film barrier blocks wind chill and repels moisture, providing an additional layer of protection against the elements for wet or immersion-affected survivors awaiting rescue on a life raft.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">SOLAS Approved:</strong> Fully compliant with international maritime safety regulations — a required survival item in SOLAS life raft equipment packs</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Aluminized Reflective Film:</strong> High-performance aluminum plating material with thermal conductivity of <strong>≤0.25 W/m·K</strong>, ensuring superior heat retention and reflection efficiency</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Ultra-Lightweight:</strong> Weighing only <strong>85 grams</strong>, the TPA adds negligible weight to survival kits while delivering critical thermal protection when it matters most</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Compact Storage:</strong> Folds down to a small, space-efficient package suitable for storage in box or container form inside any life raft survival kit</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Immediate Deployment:</strong> Unfolds and is ready for use within seconds — no training, assembly, or tools required, even by an injured or weakened survivor</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Full-Body Coverage:</strong> Large enough to enclose an adult survivor completely, covering the head and body to minimize exposed surface area and maximize heat retention</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>The Thermal Protective Aid is a <strong>single-use item</strong> and must be replaced after any deployment or if the sealed packaging shows signs of damage, puncture, or deterioration. Inspect packaging integrity during <strong>annual life raft servicing</strong> at a certified service station. Store away from sharp objects and excessive heat to preserve the reflective film and ensure the TPA performs as intended in an emergency.</div>',
