                'image'       => '/images/products/flotation-safety-knife.png',
                'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Flotation Safety Knife. Buoyant Emergency Cutting Tool for Marine Survival and Life Raft Applications.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>Flotation Safety Knife</strong> is a purpose-built marine emergency knife designed to float on water and provide survivors with an immediately accessible cutting tool during life-threatening situations at sea. Featuring a <strong>buoyant handle</strong> that keeps the knife visible and retrievable if dropped overboard, this knife is an essential piece of survival equipment carried aboard life rafts, lifeboats, and other marine survival craft. Its safety-oriented blade design allows for fast, effective cutting of ropes, lines, nets, and webbing without the risk of accidental injury — a critical advantage in the chaos of a maritime emergency.</p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Primary Functions</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12"><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">✂️</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Emergency Line Cutting</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Quickly cuts through ropes, mooring lines, fishing nets, entangled rigging, and safety harness webbing during emergencies. Fast line cutting can be the difference between escape and entrapment in a sinking or capsizing scenario.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🌊</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Buoyant Retrieval</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">The floatation handle ensures the knife remains on the water surface if dropped, allowing survivors to retrieve it even in rough sea conditions — preventing the loss of a critical survival tool when it is needed most.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Buoyant Handle:</strong> Specially designed floating handle keeps the knife visible and on the water surface if accidentally dropped overboard during an emergency</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Safety Blade Design:</strong> Blunt-tip or hook-blade configuration minimizes the risk of accidental stabbing or puncturing of inflatable life raft tubes while still providing effective cutting performance</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Corrosion-Resistant Blade:</strong> Stainless steel blade resists rust and saltwater corrosion, maintaining sharpness and reliability throughout extended storage and emergency use at sea</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Serrated Edge:</strong> Serrated blade section enables fast, efficient cutting through thick ropes, webbing, and synthetic lines even when wet or under tension</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Secure Sheath Included:</strong> Fitted sheath or locking mechanism keeps the blade safely covered during storage and allows for quick, one-handed deployment in an emergency</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">SOLAS Kit Compatible:</strong> Sized and designed for inclusion in life raft SOLAS survival packs, grab bags, and personal flotation device accessory pockets</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>Rinse the knife and sheath thoroughly with fresh water after any exposure to saltwater to prevent corrosion of the blade and sheath fittings. Dry completely before returning to storage to avoid moisture buildup inside the sheath. Inspect the blade edge for dullness or corrosion during <strong>annual life raft servicing</strong> and replace immediately if the blade shows signs of pitting, rust, or reduced sharpness that could compromise cutting performance in an emergency.</div>',
