                'image'       => '/images/products/anti-seasickness-pills.png',
                'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Anti-Sickness Pills. Emergency Motion Sickness Tablets for Life Raft and Marine Survival Kits.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>Marine Anti-Sickness Pills</strong> are emergency motion sickness tablets formulated to prevent and relieve the debilitating effects of seasickness in survivors aboard life rafts and lifeboats. In a survival situation at sea, motion sickness can rapidly accelerate dehydration, weaken survivors physically, and severely impair judgment and the ability to perform critical survival tasks. These tablets provide fast-acting relief, helping survivors maintain their physical condition, conserve vital fluids, and stay alert during the critical hours and days while awaiting rescue. A standard required item in <strong>SOLAS Pack A and Pack B</strong> life raft survival kits.</p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Primary Functions</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12"><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🤢</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Seasickness Prevention</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Taken before or at the onset of motion sickness symptoms, the tablets suppress nausea and vomiting caused by the constant motion of a life raft on open water — preserving the survivor\'s ability to function and assist in rescue efforts.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">💪</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Survival Capacity Maintenance</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">By preventing vomiting and nausea, the pills help survivors retain consumed water and food rations — directly supporting hydration and nutrition levels that are essential for maintaining strength and mental clarity during a prolonged survival situation.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">SOLAS Compliant:</strong> Meets international maritime safety regulations as a mandatory medical supply item in SOLAS Pack A and Pack B life raft survival kits</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Fast-Acting Formula:</strong> Rapidly absorbed to provide quick onset relief from nausea, dizziness, and vomiting associated with the irregular motion of survival craft on open water</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Individually Sealed Tablets:</strong> Hygienically packaged to maintain potency and protect against moisture, saltwater exposure, and humidity throughout the life raft service period</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Compact &amp; Lightweight:</strong> Small tablet form occupies minimal space within the survival kit while providing multiple doses for extended survival scenarios</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Extended Shelf Life:</strong> Formulated and packaged for long-term storage within sealed survival kits, maintaining pharmaceutical effectiveness until the expiry date</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Simple Administration:</strong> Standard oral tablet format requires no medical training to administer — clear dosage instructions allow any survivor to self-medicate safely</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>Check the expiry date of anti-sickness pills during every <strong>annual life raft servicing</strong> at a certified service station and replace immediately if expired or if packaging integrity has been compromised. Store the tablets in their original sealed packaging away from direct heat and moisture. Never use tablets from damaged or swollen packaging, as pharmaceutical effectiveness and safety cannot be guaranteed.</div>',
