               'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Fishing Tackles. Emergency Survival Fishing Kit for Life Raft and Marine Survival Applications.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>Marine Survival Fishing Tackles</strong> is a compact emergency fishing kit packaged in a durable, waterproof container designed for use in life raft survival situations. When emergency rations are exhausted or running low, the ability to catch fish becomes a critical means of supplementing food and fluid intake — raw fish providing both nutrition and moisture to survivors adrift at sea. This self-contained kit provides all the essential tackle components needed to attempt fishing from a life raft, packaged in an <strong>orange-capped waterproof canister</strong> for easy identification and reliable protection against saltwater and humidity. A standard inclusion in <strong>SOLAS Pack A</strong> life raft survival kits.</p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Kit Contents</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12"><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🎣</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Fishing Line &amp; Hooks</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Includes fishing line and hook sets for deploying baited lines from the life raft. Multiple hook sizes allow survivors to target a range of fish species found in open ocean and coastal waters.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🪝</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Bait &amp; Tackle Components</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Supplied with artificial bait and additional tackle components to maximize fishing effectiveness without the need for natural bait. Contents are pre-measured and ready to use straight from the canister.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">SOLAS Compliant:</strong> Meets international maritime survival equipment requirements as a standard inclusion in SOLAS Pack A life raft survival kits</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Waterproof Canister:</strong> All components are stored in a sealed, waterproof cylindrical container with a secure screw-top orange cap, protecting contents from saltwater ingress and humidity</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Complete Kit:</strong> Contains fishing line, hooks, artificial bait, and tackle accessories — everything needed to begin fishing immediately without any additional equipment</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">High-Visibility Packaging:</strong> Bright orange cap and white canister body allow for fast identification within a life raft survival kit, even in low-light or chaotic conditions</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Compact &amp; Lightweight:</strong> Space-efficient canister design fits neatly within life raft survival kit packaging without adding unnecessary bulk or weight</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">No Experience Required:</strong> Simple hand-line fishing method requires no rods or reels — usable by any survivor regardless of prior fishing experience</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>Inspect the fishing tackle canister during <strong>annual life raft servicing</strong> to ensure the screw-top seal remains intact and airtight. Check that all internal components are present, undamaged, and free from corrosion or moisture damage. Replace the entire kit if the canister seal is compromised or if any components show signs of deterioration, as tackle integrity is essential for survival fishing effectiveness.</div>',
