            [
                'name'        => 'Identification Tube',
                'category'    => 'Emergency Life Raft Equipments',
                'image'       => '/images/products/identification-tube.png',
                'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Identification Tube. Waterproof Emergency Document Holder for Marine Survival and Life Raft Kits.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>Marine Identification Tube</strong> is a compact, waterproof cylindrical container designed to safely store and protect critical personal identification documents, vessel registration papers, and emergency information during a maritime survival situation. Worn around the neck via an attached <strong>red lanyard</strong>, the identification tube ensures that vital documents remain on the survivor\'s person and protected from seawater, rain, and physical damage throughout the rescue process. Featuring clear pictogram instructions printed directly on the tube body, it is immediately usable by any survivor without prior training. A standard survival accessory included in life raft and emergency grab bag kits.</p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Primary Functions</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12"><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🪪</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Document Protection</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Keeps personal identification documents, passport copies, vessel details, and emergency contact information sealed and fully protected from saltwater, rain, and humidity — ensuring documents remain legible and intact when presented to rescue authorities.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🆔</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Survivor Identification</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Worn around the neck, the tube allows rescue personnel to quickly identify survivors and access critical medical, personal, and vessel information — accelerating the rescue coordination process and improving post-rescue medical response.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Waterproof Sealed Construction:</strong> Airtight tube body with a secure red cap creates a fully waterproof enclosure that protects documents even during full water immersion</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Neck Lanyard Included:</strong> Attached bright red lanyard allows the tube to be worn securely around the neck, keeping identification on the survivor\'s person at all times throughout the emergency</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Pictogram Usage Instructions:</strong> Step-by-step pictogram instructions printed directly on the tube body guide survivors on correct use without the need for written language or prior training</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Lightweight &amp; Compact:</strong> Slim cylindrical form is comfortable to wear for extended periods and adds no significant weight or bulk to the survivor</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Durable Materials:</strong> Constructed from robust, saltwater-resistant materials capable of withstanding prolonged exposure to harsh marine conditions without cracking or degradation</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">High-Visibility Design:</strong> Red cap and lanyard ensure the tube is easily spotted by rescue personnel on survivors in the water or aboard a life raft</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>Inspect the identification tube and lanyard during <strong>annual life raft servicing</strong> or grab bag checks for signs of cracking, seal deterioration, or lanyard wear. Ensure the cap seals securely with no play or looseness that could allow water ingress. Replace tubes with compromised seals immediately. Pre-load the tube with an up-to-date copy of identification documents and vessel information so it is ready for immediate use in an emergency.</div>',
