            [
                'name'        => 'Safety Valve',
                'category'    => 'Emergency Life Raft Equipments',
                'image'       => '/images/products/safety-valve.png',
                'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Safety Valve. Pressure Relief and Inflation Control Valve for Life Raft and Marine Inflatable Equipment.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>Marine Safety Valve</strong> is a critical pressure management component designed to regulate and protect the inflation system of life rafts, inflatable lifeboats, and other marine inflatable survival equipment. Constructed from <strong>high-durability orange-coated housing</strong> with a secured black rubber cap and stainless steel fittings, this valve automatically releases excess pressure when internal buoyancy tube pressure exceeds safe operating limits — preventing over-inflation damage to the raft structure while maintaining the minimum pressure required for survivor buoyancy and stability. An essential component in any SOLAS-compliant inflatable survival craft inflation system.</p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Primary Functions</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12"><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">⚙️</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Pressure Relief</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Automatically vents excess gas pressure from inflatable buoyancy chambers when internal pressure rises beyond safe thresholds — such as during temperature increases or over-inflation — protecting the structural integrity of the life raft tubes from bursting or seam failure.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🛟</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Inflation System Control</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Maintains optimal operating pressure within the life raft inflation system, ensuring buoyancy chambers remain firm and fully functional throughout the survival period while preventing dangerous pressure buildup that could compromise survivor safety.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Automatic Pressure Relief:</strong> Pre-set relief mechanism activates automatically when pressure exceeds safe limits — no manual intervention or monitoring required from survivors</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">High-Visibility Orange Housing:</strong> Bright orange body ensures the valve is easily identifiable during inspection, servicing, and emergency maintenance aboard the life raft</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Protective Rubber Cap:</strong> Black rubber dust and water cap shields the valve seat and internal mechanism from saltwater ingress, debris, and contamination during storage and deployment</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Stainless Steel Fittings:</strong> Corrosion-resistant stainless steel port fittings and retaining hardware ensure long-term reliability in the harshest saltwater marine environments</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Tethered Cap Design:</strong> Cap is secured to the valve body via a retaining cord, preventing loss of the protective cover during deployment or manual inspection at sea</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Multi-Port Flange Mounting:</strong> Robust flanged base with multiple bolt holes provides secure, leak-free mounting to life raft tube fabric or inflation system manifolds</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>The safety valve must be inspected, tested, and if necessary replaced during <strong>annual life raft servicing</strong> at a certified service station. Check that the valve seat is clean and free from salt crystal buildup, debris, or corrosion that could prevent correct sealing or relief activation. Ensure the rubber cap and retaining cord are intact and undamaged. Never attempt to adjust the pre-set relief pressure — factory calibration must be maintained to ensure the valve operates within the correct pressure range for the specific life raft model.</div>',
