            [
                'name'        => 'Rescue Quiot',
                'category'    => 'Emergency Life Raft Equipments',
                'image'       => '/images/products/rescue-quiot.png',
                'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Rescue Quoit. Buoyant Throwing Ring with Line for Man Overboard and Life Raft Rescue Operations.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>Marine Rescue Quoit</strong> is a high-visibility buoyant throwing ring attached to a length of bright orange floating line, designed to be thrown to a person in the water during a man overboard or life raft rescue situation. When a survivor is spotted in the water within throwing range, the quoit provides an immediate, reliable means of establishing a physical connection between the rescuer and the person in distress — allowing the survivor to be pulled to safety without requiring anyone else to enter the water. Its <strong>vivid orange color</strong> ensures maximum visibility against the sea surface in all weather and lighting conditions. A standard rescue aid carried aboard life rafts, lifeboats, and vessel decks in compliance with <strong>SOLAS regulations</strong>.</p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Primary Functions</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12"><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🪃</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Throwing Rescue Aid</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">The weighted ring is thrown accurately toward a person in the water, allowing them to grasp the quoit or line and be pulled to safety. The aerodynamic ring form enables reliable long-distance throws even in strong wind conditions.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🌊</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Survivor Recovery Line</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">The attached floating orange line remains on the water surface after the throw, giving the survivor a continuous line to grip and follow back to the craft. The line also allows rescuers to haul an exhausted or injured survivor back without physical contact.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Buoyant Ring Construction:</strong> Lightweight foam or hollow plastic ring floats on the water surface, remaining visible and accessible to the survivor after the throw</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Floating Orange Line:</strong> High-tenacity polypropylene floating line stays on the water surface and does not tangle or sink — maintaining a clear, graspable lifeline between survivor and rescuer at all times</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">High-Visibility Orange Color:</strong> Vivid orange coloring on both the ring and line maximizes visibility against sea, sky, and breaking wave backgrounds in all weather and light conditions</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Aerodynamic Throw Design:</strong> The ring form provides weight and aerodynamic stability for accurate long-distance throwing, even in adverse wind conditions common in open water emergencies</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Saltwater Resistant:</strong> All materials are resistant to saltwater, UV degradation, and prolonged marine exposure — maintaining strength and buoyancy throughout the life raft service period</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">SOLAS Kit Compatible:</strong> Sized and coiled for compact storage within life raft survival kit packaging and deck-mounted rescue equipment stations</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>Inspect the rescue quoit ring and line during <strong>annual life raft servicing</strong> for signs of UV degradation, fraying, weakening, or loss of buoyancy. Check that the line is properly coiled and free from tangles or knots that could impair a fast, clean throw in an emergency. Rinse with fresh water after any saltwater exposure and allow to dry fully before restoring to storage. Replace immediately if the line shows reduced tensile strength or the ring shows cracking or loss of buoyancy.</div>',
