            [
                'name'        => 'Sea Anchor',
                'category'    => 'Emergency Life Raft Equipments',
                'image'       => '/images/products/sea-anchor.png',
               'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Sea Anchor. Drift-Reducing Drogue for Life Raft and Lifeboat Survival Stability.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>Marine Sea Anchor</strong> is a fabric drogue device deployed underwater from a life raft or lifeboat to dramatically reduce drift speed and stabilize the craft against the effects of wind, waves, and surface currents. Constructed from <strong>heavy-duty canvas or woven fabric</strong> with a robust natural fiber deployment and retrieval line fitted with stainless steel thimble ends, the sea anchor acts as an underwater parachute — creating drag that keeps the survival craft bow-on to oncoming waves, reducing the risk of capsizing and minimizing drift away from the vessel\'s last known position. A mandatory item in <strong>SOLAS Pack A and Pack B</strong> life raft survival kits and an essential piece of equipment for any offshore survival situation.</p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Primary Functions</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12"><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">⚓</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Drift Reduction</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Deployed underwater ahead of the life raft, the sea anchor creates significant hydrodynamic drag that slows the rate of drift caused by surface winds and currents — keeping survivors closer to their last known position and within the search area of rescue vessels and aircraft.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🌊</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Capsize Prevention</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">By holding the bow of the life raft into the oncoming sea, the sea anchor prevents the craft from broaching and rolling broadside to breaking waves — significantly reducing the risk of capsizing in rough sea conditions and improving survivor safety and comfort.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">SOLAS Compliant:</strong> Meets international maritime survival equipment regulations as a mandatory item in SOLAS Pack A and Pack B life raft survival kits</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Heavy-Duty Fabric Construction:</strong> Robust woven canvas drogue body withstands the constant hydrodynamic loading of open ocean deployment without tearing, collapsing, or losing effective drag shape</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Natural Fiber Deployment Line:</strong> Heavy twisted natural or synthetic fiber rope provides the strength and flexibility needed to absorb shock loads from wave action without snapping or parting under tension</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Stainless Steel Thimble Ends:</strong> Metal thimble fittings at line terminations prevent chafe and wear at critical connection points, maintaining line integrity throughout extended deployment</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Simple Deployment:</strong> The sea anchor can be deployed quickly by any survivor by paying out the line over the bow — no technical knowledge or tools required for effective operation</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Compact Stowage:</strong> Folds and coils into a compact bundle for efficient storage within life raft survival kit packaging until needed</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>Inspect the sea anchor fabric, deployment line, and thimble fittings during <strong>annual life raft servicing</strong> for signs of rot, chafe, UV degradation, or corrosion. Pay particular attention to the line terminations and any stitched seams on the drogue fabric, as these are the highest stress points during deployment. Rinse thoroughly with fresh water after any seawater exposure and allow to dry completely before re-stowing to prevent mildew and fiber degradation. Replace immediately if fabric tears, line fraying, or fitting corrosion is detected.</div>',
