            [
                'name'        => 'Daylight Signal Mirror',
                'category'    => 'Emergency Life Raft Equipments',
                'image'       => '/images/products/daylight-signal-mirror.png',
                'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Daylight Signal Mirror. Heliograph Signalling Mirror for Visual Distress and Rescue Location at Sea.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>Marine Daylight Signal Mirror</strong>, also known as a <strong>heliograph mirror</strong>, is a compact, lightweight signalling device that uses reflected sunlight to produce a powerful, long-range visual distress signal visible to rescue aircraft, vessels, and coastguard stations over distances of several miles. Requiring no batteries, fuel, or mechanical parts, it is one of the most reliable and effective non-pyrotechnic distress signalling tools available to survivors. The mirror is supplied with a <strong>bilingual instruction card</strong> and bright orange backing panel for quick identification within a survival kit, and features a sighting hole and aiming technique printed directly on the device for accurate signal direction. A standard survival signalling item carried in life raft and emergency grab bag kits.</p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Primary Functions</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12"><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">☀️</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Sunlight Signal Reflection</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Reflects direct or indirect sunlight into a concentrated, highly visible flash signal that can be aimed at distant aircraft or vessels. The reflected signal is detectable at distances of up to 10 nautical miles or more under clear conditions — far exceeding the range of handheld flares in daylight.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">✈️</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Aircraft & Vessel Attraction</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">The intermittent flashing signal produced by the mirror is immediately recognizable as a distress signal to trained search and rescue crews aboard aircraft and vessels, providing survivors with an effective means of attracting attention during daylight hours without consuming limited pyrotechnic supplies.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">No Power Required:</strong> Operates entirely on reflected sunlight — completely independent of batteries, fuel, or mechanical systems, making it reliable throughout any length of survival situation</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Long-Range Visibility:</strong> High-reflectivity mirror surface produces a concentrated light signal detectable at distances of several nautical miles under clear daylight conditions</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Sighting Hole Design:</strong> Central aiming aperture allows survivors to accurately direct the reflected signal toward a specific target — aircraft, vessel, or horizon — using the printed aiming technique</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Printed Usage Instructions:</strong> Clear bilingual pictogram and text instructions printed directly on the mirror card guide survivors through correct signalling technique without prior training</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">High-Visibility Orange Backing:</strong> Bright orange reverse panel doubles as a secondary visual signal and allows rapid identification of the mirror within a survival kit in an emergency</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Compact &amp; Lightweight:</strong> Card-sized form factor fits easily within life raft survival kit packaging, grab bags, and personal immersion suit pockets without adding meaningful weight or bulk</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>Inspect the signal mirror during <strong>annual life raft servicing</strong> for scratches, tarnishing, or surface corrosion that could reduce reflective efficiency. Keep the mirror surface clean and free from salt deposits by storing it in its protective sleeve or packaging at all times. Do not clean with abrasive materials — use only a soft cloth to avoid scratching the reflective surface. Replace immediately if the mirror surface is significantly scratched, pitted, or has lost its high-reflectivity finish, as reduced reflectivity directly impacts the effective signalling range.</div>',
