                'image'       => '/images/products/waterproof-torch.png',
                'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Waterproof Torch. Heavy-Duty Marine Survival Flashlight for Life Raft and Emergency Use at Sea.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>Marine Waterproof Torch</strong> is a robust, submersible flashlight designed specifically for use in maritime survival situations aboard life rafts, lifeboats, and other marine survival craft. Featuring a <strong>rugged rubberized black body with a high-visibility yellow identification band</strong> and a wrist lanyard for secure retention, this torch delivers reliable illumination during nighttime survival situations — enabling survivors to signal rescuers, read survival instructions, perform essential tasks inside the raft, and maintain awareness of their surroundings in complete darkness at sea. A standard required item in <strong>SOLAS Pack A and Pack B</strong> life raft survival kits.</p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Primary Functions</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12"><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🔦</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Nighttime Illumination</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Provides essential white light illumination inside the life raft canopy and across the surrounding water surface during hours of darkness — enabling survivors to read instructions, administer first aid, manage equipment, and maintain visual awareness of their environment.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🚁</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Rescue Signalling</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Used to signal the position of the life raft to approaching rescue vessels and aircraft during nighttime operations. The torch beam can be aimed directly at a rescue craft or flashed in the international distress pattern to attract attention and guide rescuers to the survivors.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">SOLAS Compliant:</strong> Meets international maritime survival equipment regulations as a mandatory illumination device in SOLAS Pack A and Pack B life raft survival kits</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Waterproof Construction:</strong> Fully sealed against water ingress to a defined submersion depth — maintains full functionality when wet, splashed, or temporarily submerged during deployment or use at sea</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Rubberized Grip Body:</strong> Textured rubber outer housing provides a secure, non-slip grip even with wet or cold hands in adverse survival conditions</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">High-Visibility Yellow Band:</strong> Contrasting yellow identification ring allows the torch to be quickly located within a life raft survival kit or on the raft floor in low-light conditions</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Wrist Retention Lanyard:</strong> Attached lanyard loop keeps the torch secured to the user\'s wrist, preventing loss overboard during use in rough sea conditions</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Simple One-Hand Operation:</strong> Straightforward on/off switching allows immediate activation by any survivor regardless of physical condition, gloves, or experience level</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>Test the torch for correct operation and check battery charge level during <strong>annual life raft servicing</strong>. Replace batteries with fresh cells of the correct type and rating before repacking, even if existing batteries appear partially charged — degraded batteries may fail to perform in cold survival temperatures. Inspect the lens, rubber seals, and body for cracks or deterioration that could compromise waterproof integrity. Clean the lens and battery contacts with a dry cloth and apply a thin layer of silicone grease to sealing rings to maintain waterproof performance.</div>',
