h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">In manual mode, the wearer activates inflation by pulling the firing handle — giving the wearer full control over when the jacket inflates. An oral inflation tube is also provided as a backup, allowing the wearer to top up buoyancy pressure as needed throughout the survival period.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">≥150N Buoyancy Rating:</strong> Exceeds the minimum buoyancy threshold required to support and self-right an unconscious adult, keeping the airway safely above the water surface</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Dual CO2 Cylinder System:</strong> Twin 33g CO2 cylinders provide redundant inflation capacity, ensuring full buoyancy is achieved even if one cylinder fails to discharge correctly</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Nylon TPU Compartment:</strong> High-tenacity Nylon TPU bladder construction provides excellent gas retention, puncture resistance, and long-term airtight integrity throughout the life jacket service period</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Oxford Fabric Outer Shell:</strong> Durable Oxford fabric cover provides abrasion resistance and UV protection, maintaining the structural and aesthetic integrity of the life jacket throughout its service life</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Dual Activation Modes:</strong> Switchable between automatic water-activated and manual pull-cord inflation — adaptable to different operational environments and user preferences</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">CCS Certified:</strong> Certified under China Classification Society (CCS) or equivalent qualification standards, confirming compliance with international marine personal flotation device safety requirements</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>The inflatable life jacket must be inspected and serviced <strong>annually by a certified service technician</strong>. Servicing includes checking the automatic activation mechanism, verifying CO2 cylinder weight and charge, inspecting the bladder for leaks and seam integrity, and testing the oral inflation valve. Replace CO2 cylinders and activation cartridges as required. Store away from direct sunlight, heat sources, and sharp objects. Never use the life jacket as a seat cushion or kneeling pad, as physical compression can damage the bladder and automatic activation mechanism.</div>',
