vironment Protection</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Designed to be worn continuously throughout a working shift aboard vessels, jetties, and offshore platforms. The robust PVC construction withstands the physical demands of heavy-duty marine work environments including abrasion, chemical splash, and repeated wetting without compromising buoyancy performance.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">≥7.5 kg Buoyancy:</strong> Meets the minimum buoyancy requirement for a working lifejacket, providing sufficient flotation to support the wearer on the water surface in calm to moderate sea conditions</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Inherently Buoyant PVC Foam:</strong> Closed-cell PVC buoyant material retains full flotation performance even when wet, torn, or physically damaged — no inflation mechanism to fail or maintain</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">No Servicing of Inflation Components:</strong> The absence of CO2 cylinders and activation cartridges eliminates the cost and complexity of annual inflation system servicing, reducing overall maintenance requirements</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Durable PVC Outer Shell:</strong> Heavy-duty PVC covering provides exceptional abrasion resistance, chemical splash protection, and UV durability suited to the rigors of daily commercial marine use</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Secure Adjustable Fastenings:</strong> Adjustable straps and