ter gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🌊</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Sustained Flotation Performance</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Engineered to retain at least 95% of its rated buoyancy after 24 hours of continuous immersion, ensuring survivors remain safely supported on the water surface throughout extended rescue wait times without any reduction in flotation effectiveness.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">>155N Buoyancy Rating:</strong> Exceeds the international minimum buoyancy standard for approved life jackets, providing sufficient upward force to self-right and support an unconscious adult with airway above water</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">EPE Foam Buoyant Material:</strong> Expanded polyethylene foam core delivers consistent, long-term buoyancy performance with excellent resistance to water absorption, compression, and saltwater degradation</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">≤5% Buoyancy Loss Over 24 Hours:</strong> Rigorously tested buoyancy retention ensures the life jacket maintains effective flotation performance throughout the full duration of a survival situation</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Lightweight Design:</strong> Total weight under 0.945 kg ensures the life jacket is comfortable for continuous wear during working shifts without causing fatigue or restricting movement</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">No Inflation Mechanism Required:</strong> The inherently buoyant foam construction eliminates all activation, servicing, and maintenance requirements associated with inflatable life jacket systems</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">CCS Certified:</strong> Certified under China Classification Society (CCS) or equivalent qualification standards, confirming full compliance with international maritime personal flotation device safety regulations</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>Inspect the DFY-III life jacket before each use and during <strong>scheduled periodic maintenance</strong> for foam compression, cover fabric tears, strap fraying, or buckle damage. Rinse thoroughly with fresh water after every saltwater exposure and allow to air dry completely in a shaded, well-ventilated area away from direct sunlight and heat sources. Do not store under compression or in folded positions for extended periods, as sustained pressure can permanently reduce EPE foam buoyancy performance. Replace immediately if the foam core shows significant permanent compression, tearing, or water absorption that would reduce effective buoyancy below the rated threshold.</div>',
