xt-slate-900 mb-1">No Inflation Mechanism:</strong> Inherently buoyant foam construction eliminates all activation, CO2 cylinder replacement, and inflation system servicing requirements — significantly reducing ongoing maintenance costs and complexity</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">CCS Certified:</strong> Certified under China Classification Society (CCS) or equivalent qualification standards, confirming full compliance with international maritime personal flotation device safety regulations for both adult and child variants</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>Inspect all life jackets before each voyage and during <strong>scheduled periodic maintenance</strong> for foam compression, cover fabric tears, strap wear, buckle integrity, and whistle attachment condition. Rinse thoroughly with fresh water after saltwater exposure and allow to air dry completely in a ventilated, shaded area away from direct heat and sunlight. Store life jackets flat or hanging in a cool, dry location — never compressed under heavy equipment or stored folded for extended periods, as sustained compression reduces polyethylene foam buoyancy performance over time. Replace any jacket immediately if the foam core shows permanent compression, tearing, or water saturation that could reduce effective buoyancy below the rated ≥11 kg threshold.</div>',
