imensions:</strong> Large 480 x 280 x 560 mm buoyancy panel footprint ensures maximum foam surface area for superior buoyancy distribution and self-righting performance across a wide range of adult body types and sizes</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">No Inflation System Required:</strong> Inherently buoyant foam construction eliminates all CO2 cylinder replacements, activation cartridge servicing, and inflation mechanism maintenance — significantly reducing ongoing operational and servicing costs</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">CCS Certified:</strong> Certified under China Classification Society (CCS) or equivalent qualification standards, confirming full compliance with international maritime personal flotation device safety regulations for commercial and offshore marine operations</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>Inspect all DFY-I life jackets before each voyage and during <strong>scheduled periodic maintenance</strong> for EPE foam compression, outer cover fabric integrity, strap condition, and buckle and fastening security. Rinse thoroughly with fresh water after every saltwater exposure and allow to air dry completely in a cool, shaded, well-ventilated area away from direct sunlight and sustained heat. Store flat or hanging in a dry location — never compressed under heavy loads or stored in a folded position for extended periods, as sustained pressure can permanently reduce EPE foam thickness and compromise buoyancy performance below the rated ≥190N threshold. Replace immediately if the foam core shows significant permanent compression, water saturation, tearing, or any physical damage that could reduce effective buoyan