                'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Seawater Battery Life Jacket Light. Self-Activating Continuous Survivor Location Light for Marine Life Jackets and Immersion Suits.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>PH2703B Seawater Battery Life Jacket Light</strong> is a reliable, self-activating personal survivor location light designed for attachment to life jackets, immersion suits, and work vests to provide automatic continuous illumination during nighttime and low-visibility maritime emergencies. Uniquely powered by a <strong>seawater-activated battery</strong> that generates electrical power only upon contact with saltwater, this light requires no pre-charged battery, no manual switching, and no maintenance of electrical components during its <strong>3-year service period</strong>. Upon immersion, the seawater battery activates instantly and powers a <strong>continuous — non-flashing — light output</strong> of <strong>≥0.75 cd</strong> at a rated <strong>3.8V, 0.3A</strong> for a minimum of <strong>8 hours</strong>, providing a steady, highly visible survivor position marker throughout nighttime rescue operations. Certified under <strong>CCS or equivalent qualification standards.</strong></p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Primary Functions</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12"><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">💡</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Automatic Seawater Activation</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">The seawater battery generates power instantly upon contact with saltwater — activating the light automatically from the moment of immersion without any manual intervention. This ensures the light functions reliably even for unconscious or incapacitated survivors who cannot activate equipment themselves.</p></div><div