ss and adverse weather</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Alkaline Battery Power Source:</strong> Standard alkaline battery technology provides reliable, widely available, and cost-effective power with a stable voltage output throughout the full rated 8-hour lighting period even in cold water temperature conditions</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">CCS Certified:</strong> Certified under China Classification Society (CCS) or equivalent qualification standards, confirming full compliance with international maritime survivor personal location light safety and performance requirements</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>Inspect and replace the alkaline battery during every <strong>annual life jacket or immersion suit servicing</strong> regardless of apparent remaining charge — alkaline batteries degrade over time in storage and may fail to deliver the full 8-hour rated output if not replaced on schedule. Check the light body, lens, water-activation contacts, and battery compartment seal for corrosion, salt crystal buildup, or physical cracking that could prevent automatic activation or reduce light output. Test the light briefly during servicing to confirm correct flashing operation before reinstalling on the life jacket. Replace the complete light unit immediately if the flash frequency, light output, or activation reliability does not meet rated specifications.</div>',
