ock font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">≥ 2 Hour Burn Time:</strong> Minimum 2-hour continuous operation provides sustained position marking throughout the critical rescue window following a man-overboard incident</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">50–70 Flashes per Minute:</strong> Rapid flash frequency maximizes the light\'s conspicuity and detectability from a distance — the flashing pattern is more attention-catching than a steady light in the cluttered visual environment of a night rescue</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">30 m Drop Resistance:</strong> Rated to survive a free-fall drop of up to 30 meters — withstanding the impact of being thrown from the bridge wing or high deck of a large vessel without damage to the unit or battery</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Alkaline Battery Power:</strong> Reliable alkaline battery chemistry maintains consistent performance across the full operating temperature range and provides a stable shelf life for long-term storage on the lifebuoy station</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">CCS / Qualified Certified:</strong> Certified to meet SOLAS performance requirements for lifebuoy self-igniting lights</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Note</strong>Replace the battery and inspect the water activation switch at each <strong>annual safety equipment service</strong>. Check the unit housing for cracks, corrosion, and water ingress damage. Verify the expiry date marked on the unit — expired lights must be replaced before the vessel departs