                'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Wooden / Aluminum Spreader Step. Pilot Ladder Anti-Twist Stability Component for Safe Boarding Operations.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>Wooden / Aluminum Spreader Step</strong> is a critical structural component of pilot and embarkation ladders, fitted at prescribed intervals to prevent the ladder from twisting, rotating, or folding during use. Manufactured from either <strong>high-quality hardwood</strong> or <strong>marine-grade aluminum alloy</strong>, the spreader step maintains the parallel spacing of the ladder\'s two side ropes — ensuring that the ladder holds its correct geometry under the dynamic loads of a person boarding from a moving vessel alongside. Without spreader steps, rope ladders can twist and fold unpredictably, creating a serious entrapment and fall risk for the person transferring.</p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Technical Specifications</h2><div class="mb-12 rounded-xl overflow-hidden border border-slate-200"><div class="grid grid-cols-2 bg-cyan-600 text-white text-sm font-semibold px-4 py-3"><div>Specification</div><div>Details</div></div><div class="grid grid-cols-2 px-4 py-3 bg-white border-b border-slate-100 text-sm text-slate-700"><div class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Material Options</div><div>Hardwood / Aluminum Alloy</div></div><div class="grid grid-cols-2 px-4 py-3 bg-slate-50 border-b border-slate-100 text-sm text-slate-700"><div class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Size</div><div>1800 × 115 × 25 mm</div></div><div class="grid grid-cols-2 px-4 py-3 bg-white text-sm text-slate-700"><div class="font-semibold text-slate-900">Application</div><div>Pilot ladder &amp; embarkation ladder anti-twist spreader</div></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-8 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Anti-Twist Function:</strong> Maintains parallel rope spacing along the ladder length, preventing the ladder from twisting under dynamic boarding loads and keeping it in a safe, predictable configuration</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Hardwood Option:</strong> Traditional hardwood construction provides proven structural rigidity, natural resistance to splitting under load, and the surface grip characteristics required by SOLAS standards</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Aluminum Alloy Option:</strong> Lightweight aluminum construction provides equivalent structural performance with reduced weight and superior corrosion resistance for extended service life in saltwater environments</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">SOLAS Interval Fitting:</strong> Sized and designed to be fitted at the intervals prescribed by SOLAS Chapter V and IMO Resolution A.1045(27) for pilot ladder spreader step placement</li></ul>',
