ash conditions typical of at-sea boarding operations</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Flexible Material:</strong> Rubber flexibility absorbs shock and impact loads from heavy foot placement without cracking or fracturing — maintaining step integrity across repeated high-frequency use</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Two Size Options:</strong> Available in 28 mm and 25 mm depth configurations to suit different ladder construction standards and replacement requirements</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Safety-Critical Application:</strong> Designed for use in pilot ladder, embarkation ladder, and boarding ladder applications where step grip quality directly affects the safety of persons transferring between vessels</li></ul>',
