osure, and the marine environment</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Pressure Gauge Port:</strong> Fitted with a gauge connection port for continuous monitoring of cylinder pressure during routine inspections</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Universal Thread Compatibility:</strong> Available in standard thread specifications to fit CO₂, dry powder, foam, and clean agent extinguisher cylinders</li></ul><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Ideal Applications</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700 list-disc list-inside"><li>Replacement valve for fire extinguisher servicing and refurbishment</li><li>CO₂, dry powder, foam, and clean agent extinguisher cylinders</li><li>Marine vessel fire safety equipment maintenance</li><li>Offshore platforms, shipyards, and industrial fire safety systems</li><li>Annual fire extinguisher inspection and compliance servicing</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-amber-50 border-l-4 border-amber-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-amber-800 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold mb-1">⚠️ Important Notice</strong>Fire extinguisher valves must only be <strong>installed, replaced, or serviced by a qualified fire safety technician</strong>. An incorrectly fitted or incompatible valve may cause pressure failure, accidental discharge, or complete loss of extinguishing capability. Always verify thread compatibility and pressure rating before installation. Replace the safety pin and tamper seal after every inspection or test.</div>',
