               'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Fire Extinguisher Pressure Gauge. Accurate Pressure Monitoring for Fire Extinguisher Readiness and Compliance.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>Fire Extinguisher Pressure Gauge</strong> is a precision instrument fitted directly to a fire extinguisher valve, providing a continuous, at-a-glance reading of the internal cylinder pressure. A properly pressurized extinguisher is a ready extinguisher — the gauge allows crew members, safety officers, and inspectors to instantly confirm the unit is fully charged and operational without any disassembly or testing equipment. A mandatory component of any SOLAS-compliant fire safety inspection routine.</p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">How to Read the Gauge</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-12"><div class="border-2 border-green-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-green-50 text-center"><div class="text-2xl mb-2">🟢</div><h3 class="font-bold text-green-800 text-sm mb-1">Green Zone</h3><p class="text-green-700 text-xs leading-relaxed">Needle in green zone — extinguisher is fully charged and ready for immediate use</p></div><div class="border-2 border-red-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-red-50 text-center"><div class="text-2xl mb-2">🔴</div><h3 class="font-bold text-red-800 text-sm mb-1">Red Zone — Low</h3><p class="text-red-700 text-xs leading-relaxed">Needle below green — extinguisher is undercharged and must be removed from service and recharged immediately</p></div><div class="border-2 border-orange-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-orange-50 text-center"><div class="text-2xl mb-2">🟠</div><h3 class="font-bold text-orange-800 text-sm mb-1">Red Zone — High</h3><p class="text-orange-700 text-xs leading-relaxed">Needle above green — cylinder is over-pressurized and must be inspected by a qualified technician before use</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 