                'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Rubber Fire Hose. Heavy-Duty Marine and Industrial Rubber Fire Hose for Firefighting and Vessel Fire Suppression Systems.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>Marine Rubber Fire Hose</strong> is a heavy-duty, high-pressure flexible hose engineered for use in shipboard firefighting systems, industrial fire suppression installations, and shore-based fire stations. Constructed with a <strong>reinforced rubber inner lining, high-tenacity synthetic fiber braid reinforcement, and a durable rubber outer jacket</strong>, this fire hose is designed to withstand the extreme pressures, abrasion, and demanding conditions encountered during active firefighting operations. Resistant to heat, oil, saltwater, and UV degradation, the rubber fire hose delivers reliable, high-flow water delivery from shipboard fire main systems, hydrant stations, and portable fire pumps to suppress and extinguish fires aboard vessels and in marine facilities. Manufactured to international firefighting equipment standards for use in <strong>SOLAS-compliant vessel fire safety systems.</strong></p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Primary Functions</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12"><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🔥</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Fire Suppression Water Delivery</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Delivers high-pressure water flow from shipboard fire main connections and hydrant stations directly to the point of fire attack — enabling firefighting crews to apply water, foam, or combined agents at the volume and pressure required to suppress and extinguish shipboard fires effectively.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🚢</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Marine Fire Main System Connection</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Connects directly to vessel fire main hydrant valves, portable fire pumps, and firefighting nozzles to form the final delivery link of the shipboard fire suppression system — providing the flexible, deployable hose run required to reach fires in cargo holds, engine rooms, and accommodation spaces.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Reinforced Rubber Construction:</strong> Multi-layer construction combining a smooth rubber inner lining, high-tenacity synthetic fiber braid reinforcement, and a robust rubber outer jacket delivers the burst pressure resistance and flexibility required for demanding firefighting operations</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">High-Pressure Rating:</strong> Rated for the high working pressures generated by shipboard fire main systems and portable fire pumps, ensuring the hose performs reliably at full system pressure without ballooning, kinking, or failure</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Heat &amp; Flame Resistant Outer Jacket:</strong> Rubber outer cover provides resistance to radiated heat, hot debris, and brief flame contact encountered during active firefighting — protecting hose integrity and maintaining water flow during fire attack</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Saltwater &amp; Oil Resistant:</strong> Inner lining and outer jacket materials resist degradation from saltwater exposure, fuel oil splash, and chemical contamination common in marine engine room and cargo firefighting environments</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Flexible &amp; Kink Resistant:</strong> Rubber construction maintains flexibility across a wide temperature range, allowing the hose to be rapidly deployed, maneuvered, and directed into confined shipboard spaces without kinking or restricting water flow</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Standard Coupling Compatible:</strong> Fitted with or suitable for standard instantaneous or threaded fire hose couplings compatible with shipboard hydrant valves, fire pumps, and firefighting nozzles for rapid connection during emergency deployment</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>Inspect the fire hose before each voyage and during <strong>scheduled periodic maintenance</strong> for outer jacket cuts, abrasion, blistering, coupling corrosion, and gasket condition. After each use, flush the hose thoroughly with fresh water to remove salt, debris, and contaminants from both the inner lining and outer jacket surface. Allow the hose to dry completely before rolling and stowing to prevent mildew growth and rubber degradation. Pressure test the hose annually to the rated working pressure to confirm burst integrity and coupling seal condition. Replace immediately if the outer jacket shows deep cuts exposing the braid reinforcement, if the inner lining is cracked or delaminating, or if couplings cannot be secured leak-free under pressure.</div>',
