ghout service life</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">High Flow Rate Capability:</strong> Internal waterway dimensions optimized for the high flow rates required by shipboard fire main system pressures, ensuring maximum water delivery volume at the nozzle tip for effective fire suppression</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Ergonomic Grip Design:</strong> Shaped handle and smooth pattern-selection control allows secure, confident one-hand operation even with wet or gloved hands during active firefighting conditions</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Standard Hose Coupling Compatible:</strong> Fitted with standard instantaneous or threaded coupling inlet compatible with shipboard fire hoses, hydrant connections, and portable fire pump discharge outlets for rapid, tool-free deployment</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>Inspect the spray nozzle before each voyage and during <strong>scheduled periodic maintenance</strong> for internal waterway blockage, pattern-selector mechanism stiffness, coupling thread wear, and body corrosion or pitting. After each use or saltwater exposure, flush the nozzle thoroughly with fresh water to clear salt deposits from the internal waterway and pattern-selection mechanism. Operate the pattern selector through its full range during flushing to clear debris from the spray orifices. Apply a light coat of approved marine grease to the pattern-selector thread and coupling mating surfaces to prevent seizing. Replace immediately if the straight jet pattern is irregular, the spray pattern is uneven or blocked, or the coupling 