y delivery patterns allows firefighting crews to immediately adapt water application to changing fire conditions without interrupting water flow or releasing grip on the nozzle</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Corrosion-Resistant Alloy Construction:</strong> High-grade marine brass or alloy body and Storz coupling components provide superior resistance to saltwater corrosion, chemical contamination, and thermal stress — maintaining precision internal waterway dimensions and smooth coupling action throughout service life</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">High Flow Rate Capability:</strong> Internal waterway geometry optimized for the high volumetric flow rates generated by shipboard fire main system pressures, ensuring maximum water delivery at the nozzle tip for effective suppression of large-scale shipboard fires</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">SOLAS System Compatible:</strong> Designed and dimensioned for direct integration into SOLAS-compliant shipboard fire main systems, hydrant cabinet installations, and portable firefighting equipment sets carried aboard commercial and passenger vessels</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>Inspect the Storz spray nozzle before each voyage and during <strong>scheduled periodic maintenance</strong> for Storz coupling lug wear, locking cam condition, internal waterway blockage, pattern-selector mechanism operation, and body corrosion or pitting. After each use or saltwater exposure, flush the nozzle thoroughly with fresh water to remove salt deposits from the internal waterway, spray orifices, and Storz coupling mechanism. Operate the pattern selector through its full range during flushing to clear debris from all spray positions. Apply a light coat of approved silicone grease to the Storz coupling lugs, locking cams, and sealing gasket to maintain smooth coupling action and gasket flexibility. Inspect and replace the Storz coupling gasket at each annual service if cracking, compression set, or leakage is detected. Replace the nozzle immediately if straight jet integrity or spray pattern uniformity is compromised.</div>',
