               'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Spray Nozzle John Morris. Australian-Standard John Morris Coupling Marine Firefighting Spray Nozzle for Shipboard Fire Suppression Systems.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>John Morris Spray Nozzle</strong> is a professional-grade marine firefighting nozzle featuring the <strong>John Morris instantaneous coupling system</strong> — the Australian and Asia-Pacific adopted standard for fire hose connections widely used across commercial shipping, port fire services, and offshore marine installations throughout the region. Designed for seamless integration with John Morris-compatible fire hoses, shipboard fire main hydrant outlets, and portable fire pumps, this nozzle delivers both a <strong>high-velocity straight jet stream for direct long-range fire attack</strong> and a <strong>wide-angle protective spray pattern for crew protection and fire boundary cooling</strong>. Constructed from <strong>high-grade corrosion-resistant marine brass or alloy</strong> with a robust John Morris instantaneous coupling inlet, this nozzle provides firefighting crews with the operational versatility, coupling reliability, and high-flow water delivery performance required for effective shipboard fire suppression operations. Manufactured in compliance with international marine firefighting equipment standards for use in <strong>SOLAS-compliant vessel fire safety systems.</strong></p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Primary Functions</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12"><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🔥</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Straight Jet Fire Attack</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Delivers a concentrated, high-velocity straight water jet with the reach and penetrating force required to attack the base of fires across large shipboard spaces — including engine rooms, cargo holds, machinery spaces, and open deck areas — from a safe operational standoff distance.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">💧</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Protective Spray Screen</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Switches to a wide-angle spray pattern to generate a protective water curtain shielding firefighting crews from radiated heat and flame during approach, cooling fire boundaries to prevent spread to adjacent compartments, and suppressing flammable vapor concentrations in machinery space and fuel-related fire incidents.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">John Morris Instantaneous Coupling System:</strong> Features the John Morris snap-lock instantaneous coupling inlet — the established Australian and Asia-Pacific standard for fire hose connections — enabling fast, tool-free coupling and uncoupling in a single push-and-twist action without alignment difficulties even under emergency conditions</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Asia-Pacific Coupling Interchangeability:</strong> John Morris coupling compatibility ensures full interoperability with all John Morris-fitted fire hoses, hydrant cabinets, and portable pump discharge outlets commonly installed aboard vessels and port facilities operating throughout Australia, Southeast Asia, and the wider Asia-Pacific region</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Dual-Pattern Operation:</strong> Single-hand selectable switching between straight jet and wide-angle spray delivery patterns allows immediate adaptation of water application to evolving fire conditions without interrupting water flow or requiring two-handed operation</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Marine Brass or Alloy Construction:</strong> High-grade corrosion-resistant marine brass or alloy body and coupling components deliver superior resistance to saltwater corrosion, chemical exposure, and thermal stress — maintaining precision internal dimensions and smooth coupling action throughout the full service life</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">High Flow Rate Capability:</strong> Internal waterway geometry optimized to deliver the high volumetric flow rates generated by shipboard fire main system operating pressures — ensuring maximum water delivery at the nozzle tip for effective suppression of large-scale shipboard fires</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">SOLAS System Compatible:</strong> Designed and dimensioned for direct integration into SOLAS-compliant shipboard fire main systems, hydrant cabinet installations, and portable firefighting equipment sets carried aboard commercial, passenger, and offshore vessels</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>Inspect the John Morris spray nozzle before each voyage and during <strong>scheduled periodic maintenance</strong> for coupling lug and locking mechanism wear, internal waterway blockage, pattern-selector operation smoothness, and body or coupling corrosion. After each use or saltwater exposure, flush the nozzle thoroughly with fresh water to clear salt deposits from the internal waterway, spray orifices, and John Morris coupling snap-lock mechanism. Operate the pattern selector through its full range during flushing to clear debris from all spray positions. Apply a light coat of approved silicone grease to the John Morris coupling lugs, locking ring, and face gasket to maintain smooth coupling engagement and gasket sealing performance. Inspect and replace the coupling face gasket at each annual service if compression set, cracking, or leakage under pressure is detected. Replace the nozzle unit immediately if jet stream integrity, spray pattern uniformity, or coupling security is compromised.</div>',
