lass="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Dual-Pattern Operation:</strong> Single-hand selectable switching between straight jet and wide-angle spray delivery patterns allows immediate adaptation of water application to evolving fire conditions without interrupting water flow or requiring repositioning of the firefighting crew</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Precision Marine Brass Construction:</strong> High-grade corrosion-resistant marine brass body and Machino coupling components deliver the dimensional precision, saltwater corrosion resistance, and thermal durability required for reliable long-term performance in demanding shipboard firefighting environments</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">High Flow Rate Capability:</strong> Internal waterway geometry precision-machined to deliver the high volumetric flow rates generated by shipboard fire main system operating pressures — ensuring maximum water delivery volume at the nozzle tip for effective suppression of large-scale shipboard fires</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">SOLAS System Compatible:</strong> Designed and dimensioned for direct integration into SOLAS-compliant shipboard fire main systems, hydrant cabinet installations, and portable firefighting equipment sets carried aboard commercial, passenger, and offshore vessels operating under Japanese flag and international registry</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>Inspect the Machino spray nozzle before each voyage and during <strong>scheduled periodic maintenance</strong> for Machino coupling lug wear, snap-lock mechanism condition, internal waterway blockage, pattern-selector operation smoothness, and body or coupling surface corrosion. After each use or saltwater exposure, flush the nozzle thoroughly with fresh water to clear salt deposits from the internal waterway, spray orifices, and Machino snap-lock coupling mechanism. Operate the pattern selector through its full range during flushing to clear all spray positions of debris and salt buildup. Apply a light coat of approved silicone grease to the Machino coupling lugs, locking ring, and face gasket to maintain smooth coupling engagement and long-term gasket sealing integrity. Inspect and replace the Machino coupling face gasket at each annual service if compression set, cracking, or pressure leakage is detected. Replace the nozzle unit immediately if straight jet stream integrity, spray pattern uniformity, or Machino coupling security cannot be maintained under operating pressure.</div>',
