                'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Fire Hydrant Nakajima. Japanese-Standard Nakajima Coupling Marine Fire Hydrant Valve for Shipboard Fire Main Systems.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>Nakajima Fire Hydrant</strong> is a heavy-duty, marine-grade fire main outlet valve featuring the <strong>Nakajima instantaneous coupling system</strong> — the Japanese-standard fire hose coupling widely adopted across commercial shipping, port fire services, and offshore marine installations throughout Japan and the East Asian maritime region. Installed at designated fire hydrant stations throughout the vessel — including engine rooms, cargo holds, accommodation spaces, and open decks — this hydrant valve provides the critical connection point between the vessel\'s pressurized fire main piping system and the firefighting hose and nozzle deployment. Constructed from <strong>high-grade marine brass or gunmetal</strong> with a precision-machined Nakajima coupling outlet and robust shut-off valve mechanism, the Nakajima Fire Hydrant delivers reliable, leak-free, high-pressure water supply to shipboard firefighting crews on demand. Manufactured in compliance with Japanese Industrial Standards and international marine firefighting equipment requirements for use in <strong>SOLAS-compliant vessel fire safety systems.</strong></p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Primary Functions</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12"><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🚒</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Fire Main Water Supply Outlet</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Provides the pressurized water supply connection point between the vessel\'s fire main piping system and the deployed fire hose and nozzle — delivering the full system flow rate and pressure required for effective fire suppression immediately upon valve opening without flow restriction or pressure loss.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🔧</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Hose Connection & Isolation</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Allows firefighting crews to rapidly connect Nakajima-coupled fire hoses via the instantaneous coupling outlet and control water flow through the integrated shut-off valve — enabling hose connection, pressurization, and isolation without interrupting the fire main supply pressure to other hydrant stations throughout the vessel.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Nakajima Instantaneous Coupling Outlet:</strong> Precision-machined Nakajima snap-lock coupling outlet conforming to Japanese Industrial Standards enables fast, tool-free fire hose connection and disconnection in a single push-and-rotate action — allowing rapid hose deployment under emergency conditions without alignment difficulties or threaded connection delays</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">JIS Standard Coupling Interchangeability:</strong> Nakajima coupling outlet ensures full interoperability with all Nakajima-fitted fire hoses and nozzles carried aboard Japanese-built vessels and used by port fire services throughout Japan and East Asian maritime trade routes</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Integrated Shut-Off Valve:</strong> Built-in quarter-turn or handwheel shut-off valve mechanism allows precise flow control and complete isolation of the hydrant outlet — enabling controlled hose pressurization, safe hose exchange during operations, and complete shut-off after firefighting without tools</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Marine Brass or Gunmetal Construction:</strong> High-grade marine brass or gunmetal body, valve seat, and Nakajima coupling components provide superior resistance to saltwater corrosion, dezincification, and the elevated temperatures encountered in shipboard firefighting environments</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">High-Pressure Fire Main Rating:</strong> Valve body and coupling rated to withstand the full operating and surge pressures of shipboard fire main systems — maintaining leak-free integrity at all system pressure conditions including pump start surge and simultaneous multi-hydrant operation</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">SOLAS System Compatible:</strong> Designed and dimensioned for installation in SOLAS-compliant shipboard fire main systems, hydrant cabinet enclosures, and open-deck hydrant stations aboard commercial, passenger, and offshore vessels operating under Japanese flag and international registry</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>Inspect the Nakajima fire hydrant before each voyage and during <strong>scheduled periodic maintenance</strong> for Nakajima coupling lug wear, snap-lock mechanism condition, shut-off valve operation smoothness, body and coupling corrosion, and outlet cap or blank condition. Operate the shut-off valve through its full open-to-close range during each inspection to prevent valve seat seizure from salt deposits and corrosion buildup. Flush the hydrant outlet with fresh water after any saltwater exposure and apply a light coat of approved silicone grease to the Nakajima coupling lugs, locking ring, and face gasket to maintain smooth coupling engagement. Inspect and replace the Nakajima coupling face gasket at each annual service if compression set, cracking, or pressure leakage is detected. Pressure test the hydrant assembly annually to confirm leak-free integrity at full fire main system operating pressure. Replace the hydrant valve immediately if the shut-off valve cannot be fully closed, the coupling outlet leaks under pressure, or the Nakajima coupling security cannot be maintained.</div>',
