 and pressure required for effective fire suppression immediately upon valve opening without flow restriction or pressure loss at the point of delivery.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🔧</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Hose Connection & Isolation</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Allows firefighting crews to rapidly connect Storz-coupled fire hoses via the symmetrical instantaneous coupling outlet and control water flow through the integrated shut-off valve — enabling hose connection, pressurization, and isolation without interrupting fire main supply pressure to other hydrant stations throughout the vessel.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Storz Symmetrical Instantaneous Coupling Outlet:</strong> The symmetrical Storz coupling outlet allows tool-free, non-threaded hose connection and disconnection in a single quarter-turn action — eliminating alignment requirements entirely since both coupling halves are identical, enabling the fastest possible hose deployment under emergency firefighting conditions</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Global Coupling Interchangeability:</strong> Storz coupling compatibility ensures full interoperability with all Storz-fitted fire hoses, nozzles, and portable pump discharge outlets used aboard vessels and by port fire services worldwide — making the Storz hydrant the most internationally versatile marine fire hydrant coupling standard available</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Integrated Shut-Off Valve:</strong> Built-in quarter-turn or handwheel shut-off valve mechanism provides precise flow control and complete isolation of the hydrant outlet — enabling controlled hose pressurization, safe hose exchange during active operations, and complete shut-off after firefighting without the need for tools or additional isolation valves</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Marine Brass or Gunmetal Construction:</strong> High-grade marine brass or gunmetal body, valve internals, and Storz coupling components provide superior resistance to saltwater corrosion, dezincification, and the elevated temperatures and pressures encountered during active shipboard firefighting operations</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">High-Pressure Fire Main Rating:</strong> Valve body and Storz coupling outlet rated to withstand the full operating and surge pressures of shipboard fire main systems — maintaining complete leak-free integrity under all system pressure conditions including pump start surge and simultaneous multi-hydrant deployment</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">SOLAS System Compatible:</strong> Designed and dimensioned for installation in SOLAS-compliant shipboard fire main systems, hydrant cabinet enclosures, and open-deck hydrant stations aboard commercial, passenger, and offshore vessels operating under any flag state and international registry</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>Inspect the Storz fire hydrant before each voyage and during <strong>scheduled periodic maintenance</strong> for Storz coupling lug wear, locking cam condition, shut-off valve operation smoothness, body and coupling surface corrosion, and protective blank cap integrity. Operate the shut-off valve through its full open-to-close range during each inspection to prevent valve seat seizure caused by salt crystal deposits and corrosion buildup on valve internals. Flush the hydrant outlet with fresh water after any saltwater exposure and apply a light coat of approved silicone grease to the Storz coupling lugs, locking cams, and face gasket to maintain smooth coupling engagement and gasket sealing performance. Inspect and replace the Storz coupling face gasket at each annual service if compression set, cracking, or pressure leakage is detected. Pressure test the hydrant assembly annually to confirm complete leak-free integrity at full fire main system operating pressure. Replace the hydrant valve immediately if the shut-off valve cannot be fully closed, the Storz coupling outlet leaks under operating pressure, or coupling security and locking cam retention cannot be maintained.</div>',
