                'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Fire Hydrant NST. American National Standard Thread (NST) Marine Fire Hydrant Valve for Shipboard Fire Main Systems.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>NST Fire Hydrant</strong> is a heavy-duty, marine-grade fire main outlet valve featuring the <strong>National Standard Thread (NST) coupling system</strong> — also known as National Hose (NH) thread — the American National Standards Institute (ANSI) adopted fire hose connection standard widely used across commercial shipping, port fire services, coast guard installations, and offshore marine facilities throughout the United States, the Americas, and international vessels operating under US flag or calling at American ports. Installed at designated fire hydrant stations throughout the vessel — including engine rooms, cargo holds, accommodation spaces, and open decks — this hydrant valve provides the critical pressurized connection point between the vessel\'s fire main piping system and the firefighting hose and nozzle deployment. Constructed from <strong>high-grade corrosion-resistant marine brass or gunmetal</strong> with a precision-machined NST threaded coupling outlet and robust shut-off valve mechanism, the NST Fire Hydrant delivers reliable, leak-free, high-pressure water supply to shipboard firefighting crews on demand. Manufactured in compliance with ANSI and international marine firefighting equipment standards for use in <strong>SOLAS-compliant vessel fire safety systems.</strong></p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Primary Functions</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12"><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🚒</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Fire Main Water Supply Outlet</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Provides the pressurized water supply connection point between the vessel\'s fire main piping system and the deployed fire hose and nozzle — delivering the full system flow rate and pressure required for effective fire suppression immediately upon valve opening without flow restriction or pressure loss at the point of delivery.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🔧</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Hose Connection & Isolation</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Allows firefighting crews to connect NST-threaded fire hoses directly to the hydrant outlet and control water flow through the integrated shut-off valve — enabling hose connection, pressurization, and isolation without interrupting fire main supply pressure to other hydrant stations throughout the vessel.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">NST National Standard Thread Coupling Outlet:</strong> Precision-machined National Standard Thread (NST/NH) coupling outlet conforming to ANSI standards provides a secure, leak-free threaded hose connection compatible with the American standard fire hose coupling system used by US port fire services, coast guard stations, and vessels operating under US flag registry</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">ANSI Standard Coupling Interchangeability:</strong> NST coupling outlet ensures full interoperability with all NST/NH-threaded fire hoses, nozzles, and portable pump discharge outlets carried aboard US-flag vessels and used by port fire services and coast guard stations at American ports and throughout the Americas</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Integrated Shut-Off Valve:</strong> Built-in quarter-turn or handwheel shut-off valve mechanism provides precise flow control and complete isolation of the hydrant outlet — enabling controlled hose pressurization, safe hose connection under pressure, and complete shut-off after firefighting operations without the need for additional isolation valves or tools</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Marine Brass or Gunmetal Construction:</strong> High-grade marine brass or gunmetal body, valve internals, and NST coupling outlet provide superior resistance to saltwater corrosion, dezincification, and the elevated temperatures and pressures encountered during active shipboard firefighting operations</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">High-Pressure Fire Main Rating:</strong> Valve body and NST coupling outlet rated to withstand the full operating and surge pressures of shipboard fire main systems — maintaining complete leak-free integrity under all system pressure conditions including pump start surge and simultaneous multi-hydrant deployment scenarios</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">SOLAS System Compatible:</strong> Designed and dimensioned for installation in SOLAS-compliant shipboard fire main systems, hydrant cabinet enclosures, and open-deck hydrant stations aboard commercial, passenger, and offshore vessels operating under US flag and international registry calling at American ports</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>Inspect the NST fire hydrant before each voyage and during <strong>scheduled periodic maintenance</strong> for NST thread condition, shut-off valve operation smoothness, body and coupling surface corrosion, internal waterway blockage, and protective cap or plug integrity. Operate the shut-off valve through its full open-to-close range during each inspection to prevent valve seat seizure caused by salt crystal deposits and corrosion buildup on valve internals. Flush the hydrant outlet with fresh water after any saltwater exposure and apply a light coat of approved thread lubricant to the NST coupling thread and valve stem to maintain smooth hose connection and valve operation. Inspect the NST thread for corrosion, impact damage, or cross-threading that could prevent a secure, leak-free hose connection and replace the hydrant immediately if thread integrity is compromised. Pressure test the hydrant assembly annually to confirm complete leak-free integrity at full fire main system operating pressure. Replace the hydrant valve immediately if the shut-off valve cannot be fully closed, the NST coupling outlet leaks under operating pressure, or thread damage prevents secure fire hose connection.</div>',
