is, Storz-to-Machino, and other coupling combination interfaces — providing the broadest possible international interoperability coverage for vessels operating on global trade routes and calling at ports worldwide</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Full-Pressure Rated Construction:</strong> Adaptor body and both coupling interfaces precision-rated to withstand the full operating and surge pressures of shipboard fire main systems — maintaining complete leak-free integrity under all system pressure conditions without flow restriction or pressure drop across the adaptor body during active firefighting operations</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Marine Brass or Gunmetal Body:</strong> High-grade marine brass or gunmetal construction provides superior resistance to saltwater corrosion, dezincification, and the thermal and mechanical stresses encountered during active shipboard firefighting operations and prolonged marine environment storage conditions</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Compact & Lightweight Design:</strong> Compact adaptor form factor allows efficient storage within hydrant cabinet enclosures, firefighting equipment lockers, and portable firefighting kit bags without adding significant weight or bulk to the overall firefighting equipment complement carried aboard the vessel</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">SOLAS System Compatible:</strong> Designed and dimensioned for use within SOLAS-compliant shipboard fire main systems and firefighting equipment sets aboard commercial, passenger, and offshore vessels operating under any flag state and international registry on global trade routes</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>Inspect the Storz fire hose adaptor before each voyage and during <strong>scheduled periodic maintenance</strong> for Storz coupling lug wear, locking cam condition and retention force, alternative coupling interface condition, body corrosion or pitting, internal waterway blockage, and face gasket integrity on both coupling interfaces. After each use or saltwater exposure, flush the adaptor thoroughly with fresh water to remove salt deposits from the internal waterway and all coupling mechanisms on both ends. Apply a light coat of approved silicone grease to the Storz coupling lugs, locking cams, and face gaskets and to any alternative coupling lugs, locking rings, and gaskets on the opposing end to maintain smooth coupling engagement and long-term gasket sealing performance on both interfaces. Inspect and replace coupling face gaskets at each annual service if compression set, cracking, or pressure leakage is detected at either coupling interface. Pressure test the adaptor annually to confirm complete leak-free integrity at full fire main system operating pressure across both coupling connections. Replace the adaptor immediately if either coupling interface leaks under operating pressure, Storz locking cam retention is insufficient to prevent accidental disconnection under pressure, or body corrosion has compromised structural integrity.</div>',
