                'name'        => 'Handheld Explosionproof Light',
                'category'    => 'Fire & Emergency',
                'image'       => '/images/products/explosionproof-light.png',
                'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Handheld Explosion-Proof Light. Certified Intrinsically Safe Portable Illumination for Marine Hazardous Area and Firefighting Operations.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>Marine Handheld Explosion-Proof Light</strong> is a certified intrinsically safe portable lighting device engineered for use in hazardous areas aboard commercial vessels, offshore platforms, and industrial marine facilities where flammable gases, vapors, or combustible dust atmospheres may be present. Constructed to <strong>explosion-proof and intrinsically safe certification standards</strong>, this handheld light is specifically designed to prevent its electrical components from igniting surrounding flammable atmospheres — making it safe for use in cargo holds carrying flammable cargoes, tank spaces, pump rooms, paint lockers, engine rooms, and other enclosed shipboard spaces where explosive atmosphere hazards exist. Delivering powerful, reliable illumination through a robust <strong>impact-resistant and waterproof housing</strong>, this light is an essential tool for shipboard firefighting crews, damage control teams, tank inspection personnel, and emergency response teams operating in the most hazardous areas aboard commercial and offshore vessels. A mandatory component of the <strong>SOLAS-compliant marine firefighter personal protective equipment and tools set</strong> and essential equipment for safe operations in classified hazardous areas aboard vessels carrying flammable cargoes.</p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Primary Functions</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12"><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">💡</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Hazardous Area Illumination</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Provides safe, powerful illumination in classified explosive atmosphere zones aboard vessels — including flammable cargo holds, tank spaces, pump rooms, and paint lockers — where standard non-certified lighting devices would present an unacceptable ignition risk to surrounding flammable gas or vapor concentrations.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🔥</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Firefighting & Emergency Response</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Provides reliable hands-free or handheld illumination for shipboard firefighting crews operating in smoke-logged, zero-visibility compartments during fire emergency response — enabling safe navigation, search and rescue operations, equipment identification, and fire boundary assessment in the darkest and most hazardous shipboard spaces.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Explosion-Proof Certification:</strong> Certified to international explosion-proof and intrinsically safe standards — confirming that all electrical components, switch mechanisms, and battery systems are fully enclosed and designed to prevent ignition of surrounding flammable gas or vapor atmospheres under both normal operation and fault conditions</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Impact-Resistant Housing:</strong> Heavy-duty impact-resistant outer body withstands the drops, impacts, and physical abuse of emergency use in confined shipboard spaces — maintaining explosion-proof housing integrity and light output performance even after accidental impact during firefighting or hazardous area inspection operations</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Waterproof & Sealed Construction:</strong> Fully sealed housing to a defined IP waterproof rating protects all internal electrical components from water ingress, saltwater spray, firefighting water application, and humidity — maintaining safe and reliable operation in the wet conditions typical of marine firefighting and damage control scenarios</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">High-Intensity LED Light Source:</strong> Modern high-efficiency LED lamp delivers powerful, wide-area illumination with low power consumption — providing maximum light output and extended battery runtime to support prolonged firefighting operations, tank inspections, and emergency response activities without battery failure</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Ergonomic Non-Slip Grip:</strong> Textured, non-slip handle design provides a secure, confident grip during one-hand operation even with wet, gloved, or chemically contaminated hands — essential for maintaining control of the light during active firefighting and hazardous area operations aboard moving vessels</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">SOLAS & Hazardous Area Compliant:</strong> Certified and specified for use as part of the SOLAS-compliant marine firefighter equipment set and for classified hazardous area operations aboard commercial, passenger, tanker, and offshore vessels operating under international maritime safety regulations</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>Inspect the explosion-proof handheld light before each voyage and during <strong>scheduled periodic maintenance</strong> for housing crack or impact damage, lens integrity, switch operation smoothness, battery charge level and condition, sealing gasket condition, and certification label legibility. Any crack, impact damage, or breach of the explosion-proof housing — however minor — immediately invalidates the explosion-proof certification and requires the light to be withdrawn from hazardous area service until professionally repaired and recertified. After each use or saltwater exposure, clean the housing and lens thoroughly with fresh water and a soft cloth to remove salt deposits and contaminants. Inspect and replace housing sealing gaskets at each annual service if compression set or cracking is detected. Test the light for full output and correct switch operation before each use. Charge or replace batteries according to the manufacturer\'s schedule to ensure full battery capacity is available for emergency deployment. Never use a damaged, uncertified, or non-explosion-proof light in classified hazardous areas — the risk of igniting a flammable atmosphere is extreme.</div>',
