            [
                'name'        => 'Safety Belt',
                'category'    => 'Fire & Emergency',
                'image'       => '/images/products/firefighter-safety-belt.png',
                'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Firefighter Safety Belt. Load-Rated Marine Firefighter Personal Safety Harness and Belt for Shipboard Emergency Operations.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>Marine Firefighter Safety Belt</strong> is a load-rated personal safety and fall arrest belt system designed for use by shipboard firefighting crews during interior fire attack, search and rescue, and emergency evacuation operations aboard commercial vessels, offshore platforms, and industrial marine facilities. Worn as part of the complete <strong>marine firefighter personal protective equipment (PPE) ensemble</strong>, the safety belt provides secure attachment points for the firefighter life line, allows standby rescue crews to extract an incapacitated firefighter from a smoke-logged or fire-affected compartment, and provides fall protection for firefighters operating on elevated structures, open decks, and damaged shipboard surfaces during emergency response operations. Constructed from <strong>high-tenacity heat-resistant webbing</strong> with load-rated metal buckles, adjustment hardware, and certified attachment rings, this belt is engineered to withstand the full forces of emergency rescue extraction while remaining comfortable enough for sustained wear throughout extended firefighting operations. A mandatory component of the <strong>SOLAS-compliant marine firefighter personal protective equipment and tools set</strong> carried aboard commercial and passenger vessels worldwide.</p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Primary Functions</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12"><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🔗</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Life Line Attachment & Rescue Connection</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Provides the certified attachment point for the firefighter life line — maintaining the critical physical connection between the interior firefighting crew and standby rescue personnel at the entry point, enabling emergency extraction of an incapacitated firefighter by hauling on the life line without causing injury to the firefighter during the extraction process.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🛡️</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Fall Protection & Stability</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Provides fall arrest and restraint protection for firefighters operating at height on elevated structures, open deck areas, and compromised deck surfaces during fire emergency response — preventing falls through damaged deck sections, open hatches, and over vessel sides during the disorienting conditions of an active fire emergency.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">High-Tenacity Heat-Resistant Webbing:</strong> Belt body and attachment loops constructed from high-tenacity polyamide or aramid fiber webbing selected for thermal resistance, high tensile strength, and resistance to chemical contamination from fuel oils, hydraulic fluids, and firefighting foam agents encountered during shipboard fire operations</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Load-Rated Rescue Attachment Ring:</strong> Forged steel or alloy D-ring or O-ring attachment point on the belt front and rear rated to the full load required for firefighter rescue extraction — providing a secure, certified connection point for the life line snap hook and rescue hauling line without risk of deformation or failure under emergency extraction loads</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Secure Adjustable Buckle System:</strong> Heavy-duty metal buckle and webbing adjustment system provides a secure, snug fit across a wide range of firefighter body sizes when worn over a complete firefighter suit ensemble — preventing the belt from shifting, riding up, or loosening during physically demanding firefighting and rescue operations</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Corrosion-Resistant Metal Hardware:</strong> All metal buckles, D-rings, adjustment slides, and attachment hardware constructed from stainless steel or corrosion-resistant alloy — maintaining full load rating and smooth adjustment operation throughout long-term storage in the saltwater marine environment without corrosion seizure or strength reduction</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">PPE Ensemble Compatible Design:</strong> Belt dimensions, buckle placement, and attachment ring positioning designed for correct fit and function when worn over the complete firefighter suit, thermal protective layer, and breathing apparatus harness — ensuring compatibility with all components of the SOLAS marine firefighter PPE ensemble</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">SOLAS PPE Tool Set Compliant:</strong> Specified as a mandatory personal safety equipment component of the SOLAS-compliant marine firefighter equipment set carried aboard commercial, passenger, and offshore vessels operating under international maritime safety regulations</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>Inspect the firefighter safety belt before each voyage and during <strong>scheduled periodic maintenance</strong> for webbing condition, heat damage, chemical degradation, abrasion wear, buckle and adjustment hardware security and operation, D-ring and O-ring integrity and load rating condition, and stitching integrity at all webbing terminations and attachment points. After each use or exposure to fire, chemicals, saltwater, or firefighting agents, clean the belt thoroughly with fresh water to remove contaminants and allow to dry completely in a shaded, ventilated area before storage. Never expose the belt webbing to bleach, solvents, or harsh chemicals that could degrade fiber strength without visible external damage. Inspect all metal hardware for corrosion, deformation, or cracking that could reduce load rating below the certified rescue extraction load. Any belt that has been subjected to rescue extraction loads, significant shock loading, heat damage, or chemical contamination must be immediately withdrawn from service and replaced — load-rated safety equipment subjected to emergency loading cannot be assumed to retain its original certified performance. Replace the complete safety belt assembly immediately if webbing integrity, hardware security, or load rating cannot be confirmed to the original certified specification.</div>',
            ],
            [
                'name'        => 'Fireman Helmet',
                'category'    => 'Fire & Emergency',
                'image'       => '/images/products/fireman-helmet.png',
                'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Fireman Helmet. SOLAS-Grade Marine Firefighter Protective Helmet for Shipboard Fire Emergency Operations.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>Marine Fireman Helmet</strong> is a certified, full-protection firefighter helmet engineered for use by shipboard firefighting crews during active fire emergency response operations aboard commercial vessels, offshore platforms, and industrial marine facilities. Providing comprehensive head, face, and neck protection against the full spectrum of hazards encountered during interior and exterior shipboard firefighting — including <strong>falling objects, radiated heat, flame contact, impact, hot liquid splash, and smoke</strong> — the fireman helmet is one of the most critical components of the complete marine firefighter personal protective equipment (PPE) ensemble. Constructed from a <strong>high-impact heat-resistant outer shell</strong> with an integrated <strong>face shield or visor, inner thermal liner, and adjustable retention system</strong>, this helmet is designed to maintain full protective performance throughout the extreme thermal and physical conditions of a shipboard fire emergency. A mandatory component of the <strong>SOLAS-compliant marine firefighter personal protective equipment and tools set</strong> carried aboard commercial and passenger vessels worldwide, ensuring every vessel maintains the highest standard of firefighter head protection readiness at all times.</p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Primary Functions</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12"><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🪖</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Head & Impact Protection</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Protects the firefighter\'s head from falling objects, collapsing structural elements, low overhead obstructions, and impact hazards encountered during forcible entry, interior search operations, and structural firefighting in damaged shipboard spaces where structural integrity may be compromised by fire and heat damage.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🔥</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Thermal & Flame Protection</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Outer shell, face shield, and neck curtain provide essential thermal insulation and flame resistance to protect the firefighter\'s head, face, and neck from radiated heat, hot gas and steam contact, burning liquid splash, and brief direct flame exposure during fire attack and suppression operations in engine rooms, cargo holds, and machinery spaces.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">High-Impact Heat-Resistant Outer Shell:</strong> Thermoplastic or composite outer shell construction provides certified impact resistance and heat deflection performance — maintaining structural integrity and protective capacity when subjected to falling object impacts, radiated heat exposure, and brief flame contact during active shipboard firefighting operations</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Integrated Face Shield or Visor:</strong> Heat-resistant, optically clear face shield or polycarbonate visor provides full face protection from radiated heat, hot liquid splash, burning embers, and physical impact — deployable quickly with a single hand to allow rapid transition between protected and unprotected face configurations as operational conditions change</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Thermal Inner Liner:</strong> Multi-layer thermal comfort and protective inner liner absorbs impact energy, provides thermal insulation between the outer shell and the firefighter\'s head, and maintains a comfortable, stable fit during prolonged firefighting operations in high-temperature environments</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Neck & Ear Protection Curtain:</strong> Integrated heat-resistant neck curtain or ear flap assembly protects the firefighter\'s neck, ears, and lower face from radiated heat, hot gas contact, and burning liquid splash — closing the critical gap between the helmet lower edge and the firefighter suit collar to prevent heat injury to exposed skin areas</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Adjustable Retention System:</strong> Internal ratchet or strap retention system provides a secure, adjustable fit across a wide range of head sizes — maintaining correct helmet positioning and preventing helmet displacement during physically demanding firefighting, forcible entry, and rescue operations in confined shipboard spaces</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">SOLAS PPE Ensemble Compatible:</strong> Helmet dimensions, chin strap configuration, and neck curtain design are compatible with the complete SOLAS marine firefighter PPE ensemble including breathing apparatus face mask, firefighter suit collar, and self-contained breathing apparatus head harness — ensuring no gaps in protection between helmet and adjacent PPE components</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>Inspect the fireman helmet before each voyage and during <strong>scheduled periodic maintenance</strong> for outer shell cracks or deformation, face shield clarity and heat damage, neck curtain integrity and attachment security, inner liner condition and compression, retention system adjustment range and security, and chin strap buckle integrity. After each use or exposure to fire, chemicals, or saltwater, clean the helmet shell, face shield, and neck curtain thoroughly with fresh water and a mild detergent to remove soot, chemical residues, and salt deposits — never use abrasive cleaners or solvents on the face shield as these cause surface crazing that reduces optical clarity and heat resistance. Inspect the face shield for scratches, crazing, or deformation that reduces visibility or thermal protection — replace the face shield immediately if optical clarity is compromised. Any helmet that has sustained a significant impact, been subjected to direct flame contact, or shows deformation or cracking of the outer shell must be immediately withdrawn from service and replaced — impact-damaged helmets cannot be assumed to retain their original certified protective performance. Replace the complete helmet assembly at the manufacturer\'s recommended service life interval regardless of apparent condition.</div>',
