            [
                'name'        => 'Self-Contained Breathing Apparatus',
                'category'    => 'Fire & Emergency',
                'image'       => '/images/products/scba.png',
               'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Self-Contained Breathing Apparatus (SCBA). CCS and CE Certified Positive Pressure Air Breathing System for Marine Firefighting and Hazardous Atmosphere Operations.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>Marine Self-Contained Breathing Apparatus (SCBA)</strong> is a certified, positive-pressure compressed air breathing system that provides shipboard firefighting crews and emergency response personnel with a completely self-contained, independent supply of breathable air for operations in oxygen-deficient, smoke-filled, toxic, or otherwise immediately dangerous to life and health (IDLH) atmospheres aboard commercial vessels, offshore platforms, and industrial marine facilities. The complete SCBA system comprises seven critical components: a <strong>full face mask, backing frame and harness assembly, compressed air cylinder, medium pressure pipe assembly, high-pressure connector, positive pressure air control device, and pressure relief valve assembly</strong> — working together as an integrated system to deliver clean, regulated compressed air to the wearer on demand throughout the rated duration of the cylinder charge. The <strong>positive pressure design</strong> ensures that air pressure inside the face mask always exceeds the surrounding atmospheric pressure — preventing any inward leakage of toxic gases, smoke, or contaminants even if the face mask seal is momentarily disturbed during physically demanding firefighting operations. Certified under both <strong>China Classification Society (CCS) and CE European standards</strong>, this SCBA meets the most stringent international requirements for marine firefighter respiratory protection equipment. A mandatory component of the <strong>SOLAS-compliant marine firefighter personal protective equipment set</strong> carried aboard commercial and passenger vessels worldwide.</p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">System Components</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12"><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">😷</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">1. Full Face Mask</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Wide-vision panoramic full face mask constructed from heat-resistant rubber or silicone with an optically clear polycarbonate or tempered glass visor — providing a complete, airtight seal around the entire face to deliver positive pressure breathable air while protecting the eyes, nose, and mouth from toxic atmospheres, smoke, heat, and chemical splash.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🎒</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">2. Backing Frame & Harness</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Ergonomic back frame and adjustable shoulder, waist, and chest harness assembly securely carries the compressed air cylinder on the wearer\'s back — distributing cylinder weight evenly to minimize fatigue during prolonged firefighting operations and allowing the wearer to move freely through confined shipboard spaces.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🫙</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">3. Compressed Air Cylinder</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">High-pressure compressed air cylinder charged to rated working pressure, providing the self-contained breathable air supply for the duration of the apparatus service period. The cylinder is manufactured from steel or composite materials and hydrostatically tested to international pressure vessel standards for safe operation at full rated pressure.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🔧</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">4. Medium Pressure Pipe Assembly</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Flexible medium-pressure hose assembly connects the pressure reducer output to the positive pressure demand valve at the face mask — delivering regulated medium-pressure air from the first stage regulator to the point of breathing demand with sufficient flexibility to allow unrestricted head and body movement during firefighting operations.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">⚙️</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">5. High-Pressure Connector</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Precision-machined high-pressure connector assembly joins the compressed air cylinder valve outlet to the first stage pressure regulator — providing a secure, leak-free, full-pressure rated connection that withstands the full cylinder working pressure and allows safe cylinder replacement between operational deployments.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">💨</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">6. Positive Pressure Air Control Device</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">The positive pressure demand valve and first stage pressure regulator assembly reduces high cylinder pressure to a regulated medium pressure supply and delivers air to the face mask on demand — maintaining a constant positive pressure inside the face mask that exceeds surrounding atmospheric pressure to prevent any inward leakage of toxic or contaminated atmosphere.</p></div></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50 mb-12"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🔐</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">7. Pressure Relief Valve Assembly</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Safety pressure relief valve assembly fitted to the cylinder or regulator system automatically vents excess pressure if system pressure exceeds safe operating limits — protecting the cylinder, regulator, and connected components from overpressure damage and preventing catastrophic system failure during charging, storage, or operational use of the SCBA system.</p></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Positive Pressure Design:</strong> Continuous positive pressure inside the face mask at all times — including during inhalation — ensures that any face seal disturbance during physically demanding operations results in air flowing outward rather than toxic atmosphere flowing inward, providing the highest level of respiratory protection available</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">CCS & CE Dual Certification:</strong> Certified under both China Classification Society (CCS) and CE European standards — confirming full compliance with international maritime firefighter respiratory protection requirements and European personal protective equipment safety regulations for commercial marine operations</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Low Pressure Warning Alarm:</strong> Integrated audible low-pressure warning alarm activates when cylinder air supply approaches depletion — alerting the wearer to begin immediate withdrawal from the hazardous atmosphere with sufficient remaining air supply to safely exit to a breathable atmosphere</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Pressure Gauge Monitoring:</strong> High-pressure contents gauge allows the wearer and standby crew to continuously monitor remaining cylinder air supply throughout the operational deployment — enabling safe time management and planned withdrawal before air supply depletion</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Ergonomic Harness System:</strong> Fully adjustable shoulder, waist, and chest harness with quick-release buckles provides a secure, comfortable fit across a wide range of wearer body sizes when worn over the complete firefighter suit ensemble — allowing rapid donning and doffing under emergency conditions</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">SOLAS PPE Ensemble Compatible:</strong> System dimensions, face mask interface, and harness configuration are fully compatible with the complete SOLAS marine firefighter PPE ensemble including firefighter suit, helmet, gloves, safety belt, and life line — ensuring seamless integration of all protective equipment components</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>The SCBA system must be inspected before each voyage and serviced at intervals specified by the manufacturer and flag state requirements — typically <strong>annually by a certified SCBA service technician</strong>. Pre-use inspection must include: cylinder pressure verification against the rated charge pressure, low-pressure alarm activation test, positive pressure face mask seal test, demand valve operation check, all harness buckle and adjustment function, and high-pressure connector leak test. After each operational use, the cylinder must be recharged to full rated pressure using only clean, dry, breathing-quality compressed air from a certified breathing air compressor — never industrial compressed air. The face mask must be cleaned and disinfected after each use according to the manufacturer\'s cleaning procedure and inspected for visor crazing, seal deterioration, and exhalation valve condition. Cylinders must be hydrostatically tested at the intervals specified by the applicable pressure vessel standard — typically every 5 years. Never use, store, or transport an SCBA system with a damaged housing, leaking regulator, cracked face mask, or cylinder that has not been hydrostatically tested within its required interval. Replace any component immediately if performance does not meet the original certified specification.</div>',
