            [
                'name'        => 'Foam System',
                'category'    => 'Fire & Emergency',
                'image'       => '/images/products/foam-system.png',
                'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Marine Foam Fire Suppression System. Fixed and Portable Foam Application Systems for Shipboard Flammable Liquid Fire Suppression.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>Marine Foam Fire Suppression System</strong> is an engineered fire suppression system designed to deliver <strong>foam concentrate mixed with water</strong> as a highly effective firefighting agent for suppressing and extinguishing flammable liquid fires — classified as Class B fires — aboard commercial vessels, tankers, offshore platforms, and industrial marine facilities. By blanketing the surface of burning flammable liquids with a continuous layer of foam, the system simultaneously <strong>excludes oxygen from the fuel surface, suppresses flammable vapor generation, and cools the fuel</strong> — attacking all three elements of the fire triangle to achieve rapid knockdown and sustained fire suppression. Marine foam systems are essential fire protection installations aboard vessels carrying flammable liquid cargoes, fuel oil systems, machinery spaces with significant fuel oil inventories, and helicopter decks — where conventional water-only firefighting methods are ineffective or counterproductive against liquid fuel fires. Designed and manufactured in compliance with <strong>SOLAS regulations and international marine fire protection standards</strong> for installation aboard commercial and offshore vessels worldwide.</p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Primary Functions</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12"><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🔥</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Flammable Liquid Fire Suppression</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Delivers a continuous foam blanket over burning flammable liquid surfaces to simultaneously smother the fire by oxygen exclusion, suppress flammable vapor generation from the fuel surface, and cool the burning liquid — achieving rapid fire knockdown and sustained suppression of Class B flammable liquid fires in cargo tanks, machinery spaces, and fuel handling areas.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🛡️</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Fire Prevention & Exposure Protection</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Applied proactively to unignited flammable liquid spills to prevent ignition by creating a vapor-suppressing foam blanket over the fuel surface, and used to protect adjacent structures, equipment, and cargo from fire spread by applying cooling foam layers to exposed surfaces surrounding an active fire incident.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Foam Proportioning System:</strong> Precision foam proportioner accurately meters foam concentrate into the water supply stream at the correct application ratio — typically 3% or 6% concentrate to water — ensuring the correct foam solution concentration is maintained throughout the firefighting operation for maximum suppression effectiveness</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Multiple Foam Concentrate Compatibility:</strong> System designed to operate with internationally recognized marine foam concentrate types including AFFF (Aqueous Film Forming Foam), FFFP (Film Forming Fluoroprotein), and AR-AFFF (Alcohol-Resistant AFFF) — providing suppression capability across a wide range of flammable liquid fire scenarios encountered in marine environments</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Fixed & Portable Application Options:</strong> Available as fixed installation systems with dedicated foam monitors, deck nozzles, and distribution piping for high-risk areas, and as portable foam application equipment including foam branchpipes, inline inductors, and foam nozzles compatible with the vessel\'s existing fire main system</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">High-Capacity Foam Storage:</strong> Dedicated foam concentrate storage tank provides sufficient foam concentrate inventory for the full rated application duration required by SOLAS regulations for the protected area — ensuring the system can sustain foam application throughout the complete fire suppression operation without concentrate depletion</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Corrosion-Resistant System Construction:</strong> All wetted system components including piping, valves, proportioners, monitors, and storage tanks constructed from corrosion-resistant materials compatible with marine foam concentrates and the saltwater environment — maintaining system integrity and foam concentrate quality throughout the full system service life</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">SOLAS Compliant Design:</strong> System design, foam concentrate inventory, application rates, and coverage areas comply with SOLAS Chapter II-2 fire protection regulations and IMO guidelines for fixed foam fire extinguishing systems aboard commercial and passenger vessels</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>The foam fire suppression system must be inspected and maintained at intervals specified by the manufacturer, flag state requirements, and <strong>SOLAS annual survey requirements</strong>. Periodic maintenance must include: foam concentrate inventory level verification and top-up, foam concentrate sample testing for concentration and quality degradation, proportioner calibration verification, all valve operation and position checks, foam monitor and nozzle condition and range test, piping and connection integrity inspection, and foam storage tank internal inspection for corrosion or sediment. Flush all system piping, monitors, and nozzles with fresh water after any foam application to prevent concentrate residue buildup and corrosion of internal components. Verify foam concentrate compatibility with the vessel\'s current flammable liquid cargoes at each voyage — different cargo types may require different foam concentrate formulations for effective suppression. Replace foam concentrate that has exceeded its manufacturer\'s stated shelf life or that fails quality testing — degraded foam concentrate may produce insufficient foam expansion ratios and drainage times for effective fire suppression. Engage a certified marine fire protection service provider for annual system inspection, testing, and SOLAS survey certification.</div>',
            ],
            [
                'name'        => 'Portable Foam Applicator',
                'category'    => 'Fire & Emergency',
                'image'       => '/images/products/fire-monitor.png',
                'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Portable Foam Applicator PQ8-C. Stainless Steel Portable Foam Branchpipe for Marine Flammable Liquid Fire Suppression.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>PQ8-C Portable Foam Applicator</strong> is a high-performance, stainless steel portable foam branchpipe and tank assembly designed for the rapid manual application of firefighting foam to suppress and extinguish flammable liquid fires — classified as Class B fires — aboard commercial vessels, offshore platforms, tankers, and industrial marine facilities. Rated for a working pressure of <strong>0.25 to 0.50 MPa</strong> and equipped with a <strong>20-litre portable foam concentrate tank</strong>, the PQ8-C delivers a foam solution discharge rate of <strong>8+10% litres per second</strong> with a throw range of <strong>≥20 metres</strong> — providing firefighting crews with the standoff distance required to apply foam safely to large-area flammable liquid fires without exposing personnel to direct flame contact. The inline foam induction system draws foam concentrate from the portable tank and mixes it with water from the vessel\'s fire main system at the correct proportioning ratio — eliminating the need for a separate fixed foam proportioning installation and making the PQ8-C a fully self-contained, rapidly deployable foam firefighting tool. Constructed throughout from <strong>corrosion-resistant stainless steel</strong> for maximum durability in the marine saltwater environment. Certified under <strong>CCS or equivalent qualification standards</strong> for use in SOLAS-compliant shipboard fire suppression systems.</p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Primary Functions</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12"><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🔥</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Flammable Liquid Fire Suppression</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Delivers a high-volume foam stream directly onto burning flammable liquid surfaces to rapidly blanket the fire with a continuous foam layer — simultaneously excluding oxygen, suppressing flammable vapor generation, and cooling the fuel surface to achieve fast knockdown and sustained suppression of Class B oil and fuel fires in machinery spaces, cargo areas, and deck spill incidents.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🛡️</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Long-Range Safe Foam Application</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">The ≥20 metre foam throw range allows firefighting crews to apply foam to large-area flammable liquid fires from a safe standoff distance — protecting personnel from direct flame radiation, heat, and burning liquid splash while maintaining effective foam coverage across the full fire area from a single application position.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Inline Foam Induction System:</strong> Built-in venturi foam inductor draws foam concentrate from the portable 20-litre tank and mixes it with the water supply from the ship\'s fire main at the correct proportioning ratio — providing a self-contained foam generation system that requires only a fire main water connection for full operational deployment without fixed foam system infrastructure</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">20-Litre Portable Foam Tank:</strong> Integrated portable foam concentrate storage tank provides sufficient concentrate for a continuous foam application operation — directly connected to the inductor inlet for automatic concentrate pickup without manual concentrate feeding or separate storage vessel management during firefighting</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">≥20 Metre Throw Range:</strong> High-velocity foam stream delivery achieves a minimum throw range of 20 metres — providing the operational standoff distance required for safe foam application to large-area deck fires, machinery space fires, and cargo tank fires without exposing firefighting crews to direct flame and radiated heat hazards</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Rated Working Pressure 0.25–0.50 MPa:</strong> Compatible with standard shipboard fire main operating pressures in the 0.25 to 0.50 MPa range — ensuring correct foam solution flow rate and throw range performance without requiring pressure modification of the vessel\'s existing fire main system</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Stainless Steel Body Construction:</strong> Complete applicator body constructed from corrosion-resistant stainless steel — providing superior resistance to saltwater corrosion, foam concentrate chemical attack, and mechanical damage during storage and active firefighting use in demanding marine environments</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">CCS Certified:</strong> Certified under China Classification Society (CCS) or equivalent qualification standards, confirming full compliance with international maritime portable foam firefighting equipment requirements for use in SOLAS-compliant shipboard fire suppression systems</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Maintenance Tip</strong>Inspect the PQ8-C portable foam applicator before each voyage and during <strong>scheduled periodic maintenance</strong> for inductor orifice blockage, foam tank condition and seal integrity, applicator body corrosion, nozzle orifice condition, fire main coupling integrity, and foam concentrate level and quality in the portable tank. After each use, flush the complete applicator and foam tank thoroughly with fresh water to remove all foam concentrate residue from the inductor, internal waterway, nozzle, and tank interior — dried foam concentrate residue blocks the inductor orifice and prevents correct foam proportioning during subsequent deployments. Check inductor orifice dimensions annually and clear any partial blockage with appropriate cleaning tools. Inspect and replace foam concentrate in the portable tank if it has exceeded the manufacturer\'s stated shelf life or shows signs of separation, sedimentation, or viscosity change that could impair correct induction performance. Pressure test the applicator at the rated working pressure annually to confirm leak-free integrity across all joints, the tank connection, and the fire main coupling. Replace the applicator immediately if inductor performance, foam throw range, or foam quality cannot be confirmed to the rated PQ8-C specification during annual testing.</div>',
