                'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Siltation Boom. Environmental Silt Containment Barrier for Dredging, Construction, and MARPOL Compliance.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>Siltation Boom</strong> is an environmental protection barrier deployed in the water to contain and control the spread of suspended silt, sediment, and turbidity plumes generated by marine construction, dredging, and pile drilling operations. By physically confining the silt disturbance to the immediate work area, the siltation boom protects the surrounding <strong>clean water body, marine ecosystems, coral reefs, and fishery habitats</strong> from the damaging effects of elevated turbidity. In the Philippines, the use of siltation booms during marine construction activities is <strong>mandatory under Philippine Coast Guard requirements</strong> and is required for compliance with <strong>MARPOL regulations</strong> and <strong>DENR (Department of Environment and Natural Resources)</strong> environmental standards.</p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Regulatory Requirements</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-12"><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50 text-center"><div class="text-2xl mb-2">🇵🇭</div><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-sm mb-1">Philippine Coast Guard</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-xs leading-relaxed">Required for all marine construction activities within Philippine waters</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50 text-center"><div class="text-2xl mb-2">🌍</div><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-sm mb-1">MARPOL Compliance</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-xs leading-relaxed">Marine pollution prevention compliance for dredging and construction discharge</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50 text-center"><div class="text-2xl mb-2">🌿</div><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-sm mb-1">DENR Compliance</h3><p class="text-slate-600 text-xs leading-relaxed">Department of Environment and Natural Resources environmental standard compliance</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Silt Containment:</strong> Physical barrier prevents suspended sediment plumes from spreading beyond the construction zone — protecting surrounding water quality and marine habitats</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Marine Ecosystem Protection:</strong> Contains turbidity disturbances that can smother coral reefs, reduce light penetration for seagrass, and suffocate fish breeding grounds if allowed to spread</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Dredging & Pile Drilling Applications:</strong> Specifically suited to the high-sediment disturbance rates generated by dredging contractors, pile installation, and seabed excavation operations</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Modular Deployment:</strong> Boom sections connect to form barriers of any required length, enabling the containment perimeter to be sized and shaped to match the construction site geometry</li></ul>',
