                'image'       => '/images/products/launching-air-balloon.png',
                 'images'      => [
                    '/images/products/launching-air-balloon2.png',
                   
                ],
                'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Marine Launching Air Balloon. Heavy-Duty Inflatable Airbag for Ship Launching, Landing, and Salvage Operations.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>Marine Launching Air Balloon</strong> is a large-diameter, high-pressure inflatable rubber airbag engineered to support and maneuver vessels during <strong>ship launching, dry-docking, beaching, and marine salvage operations</strong>. Acting as rolling cylindrical supports, multiple airbags are positioned beneath the hull of a vessel, inflated to working pressure, and used to float or roll the ship from land into water — or lift and reposition a grounded or salvaged vessel. A cost-effective and versatile alternative to traditional slipways and dry docks.</p><div class="my-8 bg-cyan-700 text-white rounded-xl p-6 flex gap-4 items-start"><div class="text-3xl mt-1">⚓</div><div><h3 class="text-base font-bold mb-1">How Launching Air Balloons Work</h3><p class="text-cyan-100 text-sm leading-relaxed">Multiple airbags are placed in parallel rows beneath the vessel\'s hull and inflated to the required working pressure. As the bags inflate, they <strong class="text-white">lift the vessel off its supports</strong> and allow it to <strong class="text-white">roll forward on the rounded balloon surfaces</strong> — guided by winches or tugs — until the vessel reaches the water and floats free. The same process works in reverse to haul a vessel out of the water for maintenance or repair.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">High Load-Bearing Capacity:</strong> Engineered to support the full weight of vessels ranging from small fishing boats to large cargo ships and offshore barges</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Multi-Layer Rubber Construction:</strong> Built from multiple reinforced rubber and cord layers for maximum tensile strength, pressure resistance, and puncture protection</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Tapered Torpedo Shape:</strong> Streamlined pointed ends prevent edge stress concentration and allow smooth rolling motion under heavy loads</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Oil, Saltwater &amp; UV Resistant:</strong> Outer rubber compound withstands prolonged exposure to seawater, marine oils, sunlight, and abrasive surfaces</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Custom Sizes Available:</strong> Available in various diameters and lengths to accommodate different vessel hull dimensions and weight requirements</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Cost-Effective Alternative:</strong> Eliminates the need for permanent slipway infrastructure — dramatically reducing shipyard construction and operational costs</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Reusable &amp; Easy to Store:</strong> Deflates compactly for transport and storage between operations — reusable across multiple launches and haul-outs</li></ul><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Ideal Applications</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700 list-disc list-inside"><li>New vessel launching from shipyard construction halls</li><li>Dry-docking and haul-out for hull inspection and repair</li><li>Marine salvage and refloating of grounded vessels</li><li>Beaching and landing operations for barges and workboats</li><li>Temporary support during underwater hull maintenance</li><li>Emergency vessel recovery and offshore salvage operations</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Usage &amp; Maintenance Notes</strong>Always inspect airbags before each operation for <strong>cuts, abrasions, bulging, or surface cracking</strong>. Ensure working pressure does not exceed the rated maximum pressure for the specific bag diameter and length. After use, rinse with fresh water to remove salt, sand, and oil residue before deflating and storing.</div>',

