            [
                'name'        => 'Hall Anchors',
                'category'    => 'Docking & Mooring',
                'image'       => '/images/products/hall-anchor.png',
                'images'      => [
                    '/images/products/hall-anchor1.png',
                    '/images/products/hall-anchor2.png',
                ],
                'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Hall Anchor. Proven Conventional Stockless Anchor for Commercial Shipping and Marine Vessels.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>Hall Anchor</strong> is a time-proven conventional stockless anchor that has been the industry standard in commercial shipping for over a century. Its traditional design — featuring a shank, a crown, and two pivoting flukes that engage the seabed to resist drag — has been refined over decades of real-world service into a robust, reliable holding device trusted for vessel anchoring across all seabed types and weather conditions. The Hall anchor is <strong>stowed flush against the shell plating or frog eye</strong> of the vessel\'s bow, allowing it to be deployed rapidly and re-stowed efficiently without protruding beyond the hull envelope.</p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Proven Stockless Design:</strong> Decades of commercial service have validated the Hall anchor\'s holding power and reliability across the full range of seabed types encountered in commercial shipping operations</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Shell / Frog Eye Stowage:</strong> Designed to stow flush against the vessel\'s bow shell plating or within the hawse pipe frog eye, keeping the anchor clear of the hull during navigation without risk of damage or entanglement</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Pivoting Flukes:</strong> Two flukes pivot on a horizontal axis relative to the shank, allowing the anchor to orient itself to the direction of pull and dig into the seabed regardless of the vessel\'s swinging direction</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Commercial Shipping Standard:</strong> The Hall anchor is one of the most widely used anchor designs in the global commercial fleet, making spare parts, servicing expertise, and inspection familiarity universally available</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">All Seabed Types:</strong> Suitable for anchoring in sand, mud, gravel, and mixed seabed compositions typically encountered in coastal anchorages and port approaches</li></ul>',
            ],
            [
                'name'        => 'Stockless Anchors',
                'category'    => 'Docking & Mooring',
                'image'       => '/images/products/stockless-anchor.png',
                'images'      => [
                    '/images/products/stockless-anchor2.png',
                    '/images/products/stockless-anchor3.png',
                ],
               'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Stockless Anchor. Improved Admiralty-Derived Anchor with Dual Pivoting Flukes for Commercial and Marine Vessel Anchoring.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>Stockless Anchor</strong> is an evolution of the classic Admiralty anchor design, engineered to address the practical limitations of the stocked anchor for use on commercial vessels. By replacing the fixed stock with <strong>two flukes that pivot on the same plane perpendicular to the shank</strong>, the stockless anchor can orient to the seabed pull direction automatically — allowing it to dig in and set quickly regardless of how it lands on the bottom. The combined weight of the shank and anchor chain, or the shank angling under the tension of the vessel\'s pull, maintains the anchor in its set position by keeping the assembly flat on the sea floor and directing the load to the flukes.</p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">How It Works</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12"><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">⚓</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Dual Pivoting Flukes</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">The two flukes pivot perpendicular to the shank, allowing the anchor to automatically orient toward the direction of pull and drive both flukes into the seabed simultaneously for maximum holding power.</p></div><div class="border-2 border-cyan-400 rounded-lg p-5 bg-slate-50"><div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-3"><span class="text-2xl">🔗</span><h3 class="font-bold text-slate-900 text-base m-0">Chain Weight Setting</h3></div><p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">The weight of the anchor chain laying flat on the seabed keeps the shank horizontal under tension, directing the holding force efficiently into the flukes and preventing the anchor from breaking out under normal load.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-8 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Improved Admiralty Derivation:</strong> An engineering refinement of the traditional Admiralty anchor, addressing its stowage and handling limitations while retaining the proven holding principle</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Compact Hawse Pipe Stowage:</strong> The absence of a fixed stock allows the stockless anchor to retract cleanly into the hawse pipe, keeping the anchor fully contained within the hull when not in use</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Rapid Setting:</strong> Pivoting fluke design allows the anchor to set quickly in sand and mud seabeds, reducing the scope of chain required to achieve reliable holding</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Wide Commercial Adoption:</strong> One of the most universally used anchor designs in commercial shipping, harbor operations, and offshore support vessel fleets worldwide</li></ul>',
            ],
