                'image'       => '/images/products/mooring-buoy.png',
                'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Mooring Buoy. Heavy-Duty Floating Anchor Point for Secure Vessel Berthing and Offshore Mooring.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>Mooring Buoy</strong> is a high-visibility, robust floating marine device designed to provide a <strong>stable and secure mooring point for ships, yachts, barges, and offshore platforms</strong>. Anchored to the seabed using chains, concrete blocks, or screw anchors, the buoy remains afloat while absorbing wave and tidal forces — allowing vessels to tie off safely without docking at a pier or quay. Built for durability in harsh marine environments, it ensures reliable long-term performance in ports, harbors, and offshore installations.</p><div class="my-8 bg-cyan-700 text-white rounded-xl p-6 flex gap-4 items-start"><div class="text-3xl mt-1">⚓</div><div><h3 class="text-base font-bold mb-1">How Mooring Buoys Work</h3><p class="text-cyan-100 text-sm leading-relaxed">The buoy is <strong class="text-white">secured to a heavy seabed anchor system</strong> using mooring chains or synthetic lines. A vessel connects its mooring lines to the <strong class="text-white">top-mounted eye or bollard</strong>, allowing the buoy to absorb movement from wind, waves, and currents while keeping the vessel safely positioned in open water.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">High Buoyancy Core:</strong> Constructed with foam-filled or steel-shell bodies to maintain flotation even if outer layers are damaged</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Corrosion-Resistant Hardware:</strong> Fitted with galvanized or stainless steel shackles, swivels, and pad eyes for long-term 