                'image'       => '/images/products/cargo-net.png',
                'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Cargo Net. Heavy-Duty Lifting and Securing Net for Marine and Offshore Cargo Handling.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>Cargo Net</strong> is a reinforced, high-tensile rope net designed for the <strong>safe lifting, transfer, and securing of goods, equipment, and supplies</strong> in marine, offshore, and port operations. Commonly used with cranes on vessels, docks, and offshore platforms, it allows bulk cargo or irregularly shaped items to be lifted efficiently while preventing load shift and accidental spillage. Built for durability and repeated heavy use, cargo nets are essential for safe material handling at sea.</p><div class="my-8 bg-cyan-700 text-white rounded-xl p-6 flex gap-4 items-start"><div class="text-3xl mt-1">⚓</div><div><h3 class="text-base font-bold mb-1">How Cargo Nets Work</h3><p class="text-cyan-100 text-sm leading-relaxed">Items are placed within the net and the corners are <strong class="text-white">secured to lifting hooks or shackles</strong>. When hoisted by a crane, the net <strong class="text-white">evenly distributes the load weight</strong> across multiple rope intersections, stabilizing cargo during vertical lifting and horizontal transfer between vessels or platforms.</p></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">High-Tensile Rope Construction:</strong> Manufactured from durable polypropylene, nylon, or polyester fibers for superior strength and flexibility</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Heavy Load Capacity:</strong> Engineered to safely handle substantial cargo weights during crane lifting operations</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Reinforced Border Ropes:</strong> Strengthened perimeter lines provide additional structural integrity and secure attachment points</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Weather &amp; UV Resistant:</strong> Designed to withstand prolonged exposure to saltwater, sunlight, and harsh marine environments</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Flexible &amp; Foldable:</strong> Lightweight and easy to store when not in use, ideal for repeated shipboard operations</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Custom Mesh Sizes Available:</strong> Offered in various mesh openings and dimensions to suit different cargo types and lifting requirements</li></ul><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Ideal Applications</h2><ul class="mb-12 space-y-2 text-slate-700 list-disc list-inside"><li>Ship-to-ship cargo transfer operations</li><li>Offshore platform supply lifting</li><li>Dockside loading and unloading</li><li>Bulk goods and equipment transport</li><li>Construction material handling at sea</li><li>Emergency relief and supply deployment</li></ul><div class="mt-10 bg-slate-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 rounded-r-xl p-5 text-sm text-slate-700 leading-relaxed"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">🔧 Usage &amp; Maintenance Notes</strong>Inspect the net before each lift for <strong>frayed ropes, broken strands, or weakened knots</strong>. Never exceed the rated safe working load (SWL). After use in saltwater environments, rinse with fresh water and dry thoroughly before storage to extend service life.</div>',
