                    '/images/products/rubber-fender2.png',
                ],
                'description' => '<p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed"><strong>Rubber Fender. Marine Collision Energy Absorption Fender for Dock, Quay, and Vessel Protection During Berthing.</strong></p><p class="mb-8 leading-relaxed">The <strong>Rubber Fender</strong> is a fundamental piece of port and vessel infrastructure whose primary function is to <strong>absorb the kinetic energy</strong> of a vessel during the berthing process — protecting both the vessel\'s hull and the dock or quay structure from impact damage. As a vessel approaches and makes contact with the berth, the rubber fender deforms elastically under the berthing load, converting the vessel\'s momentum into deformation energy that is then safely dissipated as heat rather than transmitted as structural impact to either the vessel or the dock. Rubber fenders are available in a wide range of types and profiles to suit different vessel sizes, berthing energies, and dock configurations, including <strong>pneumatic, CO-type, SC-type, GD-type</strong>, and many other specialized forms.</p><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Fender Types Available</h2><div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 gap-3 mb-12"><div class="rounded-xl border-2 border-cyan-400 bg-cyan-50 p-4 text-center"><div class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-700">Pneumatic</div><div class="text-slate-600 text-xs mt-1">Air-filled floating fender for large vessel applications</div></div><div class="rounded-xl border-2 border-cyan-400 bg-cyan-50 p-4 text-center"><div class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-700">CO-Type</div><div class="text-slate-600 text-xs mt-1">Cylindrical solid rubber fender for dock face mounting</div></div><div class="rounded-xl border-2 border-cyan-400 bg-cyan-50 p-4 text-center"><div class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-700">SC-Type</div><div class="text-slate-600 text-xs mt-1">Semi-circular profile for quay edge and corner protection</div></div><div class="rounded-xl border-2 border-cyan-400 bg-cyan-50 p-4 text-center"><div class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-700">GD-Type</div><div class="text-slate-600 text-xs mt-1">Cell fender for high-energy absorption at large berths</div></div><div class="rounded-xl border-2 border-cyan-400 bg-cyan-50 p-4 text-center"><div class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-700">Solid Rubber</div><div class="text-slate-600 text-xs mt-1">Traditional long-lasting fender for general berthing</div></div><div class="rounded-xl border-2 border-cyan-400 bg-cyan-50 p-4 text-center"><div class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-700">Custom</div><div class="text-slate-600 text-xs mt-1">Specialist profiles for unique dock configurations</div></div></div><h2 class="mt-12 mb-6 text-xl font-semibold text-cyan-600">Key Features</h2><ul class="mb-8 space-y-2 text-slate-700"><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Berthing Energy Absorption:</strong> Elastic deformation converts vessel kinetic energy into safe heat dissipation, preventing structural damage to the vessel hull and dock infrastructure</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Dual Protection:</strong> Simultaneously protects both the vessel\'s hull plating and the dock or quay structure — reducing maintenance costs and repair downtime for both operators</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Long Service Life:</strong> High-quality natural or synthetic rubber compounds resist UV degradation, ozone cracking, seawater absorption, and abrasion — providing decades of service with minimal maintenance</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Wide Profile Range:</strong> Available in multiple profiles and sizes to match the vessel displacement, berthing speed, and dock geometry of any port or marina application</li><li class="pl-6 py-1.5 border-l-4 border-cyan-400 bg-slate-50/50"><strong class="block font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Readily Available:</strong> One of the most universally available marine infrastructure components — solid rubber fenders in particular are stocked globally and can be procured quickly for urgent replacement</li></ul>',            ],
